title: cheese chili cubes
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat eggs with electric mixer until light.
Stir together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add 6 eggs and mix well.
Fold in cheese, cottage cheese, chilies and bacon.
Turn into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown on top and knife inserted in middle comes out clean.
Remove from oven and let stand 10 minutes.
Cut in small squares and serve hot.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Mix salt with shredded cabbage.
Mix with hot bacon drippings. Cook on low heat until tender.
Stir to keep from burning.
Good served with steam fried potatoes.

title: ziti a la judy
directions: Have someone else clean and skin legs.
Place in plastic bag in salt water and put in freezer.
Legs won't move in the pan once they've been frozen.
Dip legs in flour, egg mixture and then in flour again (like chicken).
Fry until browned.

title: cheese frosted cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower 12 to 15 minutes.
Drain.
Place in ungreased shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt.
Combine mayonnaise and mustard - spread over cauliflower.
Top with cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted, about 10 minutes.

title: quick broccoli dish
directions: Prepare both according to directions. Increase milk in macaroni and cheese to 3/4 cup. Mix in casserole dish. Bake 20 minutes at 300°. Serve. Good, quick and easy!

title: hershey's chocolate syrup cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to creamed mixture.
Add chocolate syrup; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured sheet pan; bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: cucumber and spinach salad
directions: In a small bowl, combine sour cream, lemon juice, vinegar, salt and chives. Pour the dressing over cucumbers and gently mix to coat. Cover the bowl and chill 2 hours to overnight.

title: baked carrot squares(diabetic)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 8-inch square baking pan with vegetable cooking spray, or use a nonstick pan.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger; drain and add taco seasoning.
Add to other salad ingredients.
Add chips and Catalina just prior to serving; toss thoroughly.
Full recipe makes a very large quantity.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crust from bread.
Spread butter or margarine on bread. Place in casserole dish.
Brown sausage and drain, then spoon over bread.
Mix eggs well; add half and half, salt and pepper.
Pour this mixture over bread and sausage.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Set out about 15 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Fry ground beef.
Combine mushroom soup, milk, beef, onion, Tater Tots and Cheddar cheese in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: broiled herbed vegetables
directions: Boil potato until tender.
Line bottom of a 1 1/2-quart greased casserole dish with potato.
Dab with butter.
Layer the zucchini on top of the potatoes and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and half of the herbs.
Layer the onions and tomatoes and sprinkle with remaining herbs and more Parmesan cheese.
Add salt and pepper.
Broil in oven for about 10 minutes or until vegetables are heated and cheese is melted.

title: chocolate caramel squares
directions: Melt caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk together. Combine cake mix, butter, milk and nuts. Press half of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 6 minutes. Sprinkle on chocolate chips and pour on caramel and milk mixture. Sprinkle remainder of cake mixture on top. Bake 15 to 18 minutes. Cool and refrigerate 30 minutes before slicing.

title: ham and cheese sandwich(ideal for brunch!!)
directions: Butter bread slices and put half in bottom of buttered casserole.
Top each slice with ham and grated cheese.
Top with other slices of buttered bread, buttered side up.
Beat eggs, salt and milk.
Pour this mixture over cheese and bread.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 275° for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chili-corn soup
directions: Fry bacon crisp and set aside.
Add potatoes and onion to bacon grease and cook until onion is tan.
Add 1 cup of water and simmer until potatoes are done.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Add green chilies.
Season to taste.
Crumble bacon on top.

title: chicken yakitori(poultry)
directions: Combine soy sauce, sugar, broth, vegetable oil, ginger and garlic in medium bowl.
Cut chicken into strips about 3 x 1/2-inch.
Add to marinade and toss to combine.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: deviled potatoes
directions: Put into casserole dish.
Sprinkle
shredded cheese and bacon bits on top.
Bake at 375° until cheese melts.

title: molded cuke salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Mix jello, cucumbers, onion juice and salt.
Chill in mold.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine dry ingredients; add milk, egg and oil.
Mix just until dry ingredients are moist.
Stir in cheese, chilies and corn.
Pour into a greased 8 or 9-inch pan and bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in saucepan; stir in water.
Stir constantly over medium heat until it boils.
When it comes to a boil, boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in remaining ingredients.
Serve warm or cool.
Great on warm gingerbread!

title: crumb cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles cornmeal.
Remove 1 cup of mixture and combine with cinnamon and pecans; set aside.
To remaining crumb mixture add milk and baking powder.
Spread into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle crumb topping over batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Cut into squares; garnish with whipped topping and a pecan.

title: corn pudding
directions: Add eggs to milk.
Combine the other ingredients.
Pour in a greased baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: egg burritos
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain off fat.
Add picante sauce and stir. Add eggs, one at a time, and scramble.
Cook until all eggs are scrambled.
Spoon into tortilla shell and roll.
Wrap each shell in foil.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
May add crumbled bacon or ham or Cheddar cheese or may eliminate eggs or sausage.

title: low-fat low sodium pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with fennel, garlic powder and allspice. Drain.
Add cheese, soup, oregano, tomatoes and pepper to ground beef.
Stir in cooked noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 10 servings.

title: pop ice cream
directions: Mix thoroughly to fill line.

title: e z lasagna
directions: Brown beef and onion in a large skillet.
Drain off grease. Add salt, garlic and Prego. Cook until bubbly. Get large broiler pan or two 8 x 13-inch cake pans.
Take uncooked noodles out of the box. Divide in 2 separate piles.
Wet the first set of noodles, then the cottage cheese and 1/3 more sauce and another layer of wet noodles.
Put Mozzarella cheese and sauce on top as final layer.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 325° for 1 hour. Let cool 15 minutes and serve.

title: butter dipped bread sticks
directions: Melt butter in a cookie sheet in 450° oven.
Combine dry ingredients in a bowl.
Add milk and blend with a fork.
Batter will be stiff.
Turn onto well-floured cloth and knead a few times. Roll or pat dough to about 1/2-inch thick and cut into strips with a flour dipped table knife.
Dip in melted butter, coating both sides.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: tailgate salad
directions: Drain all vegetables.
Mix sugar with vinegar.
Pour over the vegetables and mix well.
Let set for about 1 hour before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo until tender. Add soup and cheese. Cook rice and broccoli. Drain and add to first mixture. Place in baking dish; cover and bake in microwave 8 minutes.

title: the world's best cake
directions: Mix in order listed by hand.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: kentucky cornbread
directions: Mix well. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cherry delight cake
directions: Put pie filling in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, then spread dry cake mix over the pie filling.
Spread the pecans evenly over the cake mix.
Melt margarine and pour over top.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Sift flour and baking powder; mix butter, shortening, sugar, eggs and butter.
Add flour mixture with milk.
Add milk flavoring.
Bake at 325° to 350° until done.

title: neiman's cookie recipe
directions: *Blended Oatmeal:
Mix in blender to a fine powder.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Drain potatoes.
Mix sugar, butter and vanilla into potatoes. Take a ball of sweet potatoes.
Put a marshmallow in middle.
Roll in coconut and bake at 350° until brown.

title: grandma's bean soup
directions: Put ham bone in large pot with water and bring to a boil.
Add all but the flour, paprika and oil.
Simmer mixture until vegetables are done. Bring mixture to a boil.
Add paste made from flour, paprika and oil to boiling soup.
Reduce heat to simmer until done.
Serve with cornbread or warm bread.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dump crushed pineapple into 9 x 13 x 2-inch ungreased pan and spread evenly.
Dump cherry pie filling over pineapple and spread evenly.
Dump cake mix (dry) over pie filling and spread evenly.
Spread chopped nuts over cake mix. Slice margarine into pats and place on top of cake.
Bake 1 hour and enjoy.

title: banana bran muffins
directions: Combine bran, milk and bananas in mixing bowl.
Add sugar, egg and shortening.
Stir only until combined.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake in 400° oven about 25 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix soup, onion, olives and enchilada seasoning together.
Fry tortillas in oil until soft.
Dip tortillas in enchilada sauce. Add meat, soup mixture and cheese in tortillas and roll.
Top enchiladas with more cheese and sauce and add green onions on top.

title: raspberry punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid according to package.
Add one can of orange juice in punch bowl; add 7-Up.
Add sherbet and serve.

title: scalloped potatoes and peas
directions: In a 1 3/4-quart casserole, combine potatoes, peas, green onion, soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Sprinkle with paprika.
Serves 4.

title: kneadery guacamole
directions: Mash avocados with a potato masher.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Let stand for 1 hour and serve.

title: holiday ribbon ring
directions: Step 1:
Dissolve strawberry flavor gelatin in 2 1/2 cups boiling water.
Pour 1 1/2 cups into 6 cup ring mold.
Chill until set but not firm, about 15 minutes.
Chill the remaining gelatin in a bowl.
Gradually blend in 1/2 cup sour cream; spoon over the gelatin in mold.
Chill until set but not firm, about 15 minutes.

title: creamsicle cake
directions: Add orange flavoring to yellow cake mix or use 1 box orange cake mix.
Cool for 15 minutes and put holes in cake with fork. Mix jello, boiling water and cold water.
Let cool.
Pour over cake and refrigerate for 1/2 hour.
Mix vanilla pudding, orange extract, milk, vanilla and Cool Whip.
Put over cake and refrigerate.

title: homemade buttermilk biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Mix well.
Cut in shortening with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add buttermilk, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: frozen waldorf salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Set pineapple aside.
In saucepan, combine juice, sugar, eggs and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium-low heat until slightly thickened.
Remove from heat; cool.
Stir in pineapple, celery, apples and pecans. Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into a 9-inch square pan.
Cover and freeze until firm.
Let stand at room temperature for about 15 minutes before cutting.
Serve on lettuce lined plates, if desired.
Easy to increase amount and to prepare ahead of time. Serves 12.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well and roll out in small balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: seven-minute frosting
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in top of double boiler and mix well.
Place over simmering water and beat with rotary beater 7 to 10 minutes or until mixture holds stiff peaks.
Remove from heat and blend in vanilla.
Makes enough to frost two 9-inch layer cakes.

title: pink popcorn balls
directions: In double
boiler
top, put marshmallows and butter and stir until melted.
Make
pink
with
a	few drops of red food coloring.
Pour mixture over
popped corn and shape into balls quickly with well greased hands.

title: easy mac 'n cheese
directions: Follow those words printed
so perfectly on the side of the box of Kraft Macaroni and Cheese!
They explain it better than anyone.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: In large bowl, blend sugar, butter and chocolate.
Add eggs, one at a time, until well blended.
Mix in vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add gradually to chocolate mixture.
Cover and chill 2 hours or overnight.
Drop mixture by rounded teaspoonfuls into powdered sugar, coating lightly.
Shape into balls.
Place on greased baking sheets, 2-inches apart, flatten slightly.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes or until done.
Remove and cool on wire racks.

title: curried ham and cheese sandwich
directions: Mix cheese, lemon juice and curry powder; spread on rolls. Fit ham and Swiss cheese on top; cover with roll.
Cover with foil and bake 30 minutes at 350° or until cheese is melted.

title: bourbon hot dogs
directions: Simmer sauce and add hot dogs cut into 1-inch pieces.
Simmer 5 to 6 minutes.
Put toothpick in each piece of hot dog and serve in shallow dish containing some sauce.

title: polish mistake
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Drain well; add diced cheese and stir until melted.
Add spices.
Spread on party rye.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze or place in oven at 400° for 4 to 5 minutes. Cook after frozen on cookie sheet at 400° for 10 minutes.
Serve hot.
May also be kept warm in crock-pot.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and shortening until fluffy and light. Add eggs.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to cream mixture, alternating with milk.
Stir in flavorings.
Spoon mixture into greased 10-inch tube pan and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Add glaze to cake and cool before turning out.

title: baked stuffed potatoes
directions: Scrub baking potatoes.
Puncture skins with fork.
Bake at 425° for 1 hour.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise and scoop out insides.
Mash.
Combine water, dry milk powder, salt and pepper. Add to mashed potatoes and beat until fluffy, adding more hot water if needed.
Pile lightly into shells and sprinkle with paprika.
Return to oven for about 10 minutes or until heated through.
Yields 6 servings.
Has 60 calories per serving.

title: creamed corn
directions: Combine all, except butter and flour.
Simmer for 5 minutes. Blend butter and flour and add to corn, then add pepper.

title: curry lunch sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients, except muffins.
Split and toast English muffins.
Spread with mix and broil until bubbly.

title: barbecued brisket
directions: Brown meat in salt, pepper, garlic salt and seasoned salt. Place in roasting pan.
Pour the remaining ingredients over the meat.
Cover and bake at 325° until tender (approximately 3 hours).
Add more water if necessary.
Chill meat and sauce.
Cut off all fat.
Slice across the grain (thin slices).
Place in dish. Pour sauce over the top.
Cover and freeze or chill until ready to reheat.

title: cowboy roast
directions: Put ingredients in a roaster pan in order listed.
Fill to within 3 to 4 inches of top of pan with water.
Bake at 250° for 12 hours.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare cake mix per directions.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) layer pans (layers will be thinner).
Set aside to cool.
Mix pudding according to directions.
Refrigerate to set.
Using 1/3 of each of the ingredients in order begin to layer them in 1 large glass punch bowl, starting with the cake:
1 (9-inch) cake (broken into pieces), 1/3 cherry pie filling, 1/3 fruit cocktail, 1/3 pineapple, 1/3 topping and 1/3 coconut.
Repeat 2 more times.
Refrigerate until served.
Serves 35.

title: mother's pumpkin pie
directions: Mix first 12 ingredients well and add flour and lemon extract.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes then 350° for 35 to 40 minutes (test with knife).

title: cider vinaigrette glazed beets
directions: Cut tops off beets, leaving at least 1-inch of stems.
Scrub beets under running water with soft vegetable brush, being careful not to break skins.
Place beets in saucepan; cover with water. Bring to a boil over high heat; reduce heat.
Simmer 30 minutes or until just barely firm when pierced with a fork.
Transfer to plate and allow to cool slightly.
Meanwhile, in a medium mixing bowl, whisk together oil, vinegar, horseradish, mustard, sugar, salt and pepper.
When beets are cool enough to handle, peel off skins and trim root end.
Cut beets in half, then into wedges.
Add warm beets to vinaigrette in mixing bowl.
Toss to coat.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: seaside salad
directions: Mix shrimp and crabmeat with the next 8 ingredients.
Stir in chopped Mandarin orange sections; chill.
To serve, fill avocado halves with shrimp and crab mixture.
Garnish with additional Mandarin orange sections, grapes and melon balls.
Makes 4 servings.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Crush half of the strawberries with a potato masher or fork; stir in cornstarch, lemon juice, salt and sugar.
Cook over medium heat until mixture is thickened and clear.
Cool.
Slice or cut in halves the remaining strawberries.
Fold into the cooked mixture.
Pour mixture into pie shell; chill.
Cover with whipped cream before serving.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion.
Drain.
Return to skillet; add chili seasoning, corn and salsa.
Simmer for 5 minutes and add sliced black olives, if desired.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch baking dish or similar size dish.
Mix cornbread mix with milk according to package directions.
Fold in cubed Cheddar cheese.
Pour this mixture onto meat in baking dish.
Bake in 425° oven until cornbread is done, about 30 minutes.

title: fajitas
directions: In medium bowl mix oil, lime juice, cilantro, garlic, red pepper, salt and pepper.
Pour marinade over steak.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator turning occasionally 1 to 4 days. Barbecue steak on grill brushing with marinade.
In skillet, brown green pepper and onion in butter.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients like pie dough and press in a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes and cool.
Cream together next 3 ingredients and spread on first layer.
Whip together milk and pudding and spread on second layer.
Top with the remaining Cool Whip.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar, milk and salt until it will form a soft ball in cold water. Let cool. Add peanut butter. Beat well.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Mix with creamed mixture.
Chill thoroughly and roll out.
Use cookie cutters you desire.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Frost and decorate.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger, then add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for about 1/2 hour.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook and drain broccoli; put in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Add chicken.
Mix soup, milk and cheese.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with French fried onion rings, if desired.
Bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: apricot, date and pineapple jam
directions: Put all ingredients in food processor to mix thoroughly. Store in refrigerator.
Can be used as the fruit for diabetic meal planning.

title: escalloped chicken
directions: Mix together and pour into greased baking dish.
When cutting up chicken, pull skin off and spread to dry.
Grind this and sprinkle
on top.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 90 minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; pour into casserole dish.
Top with crackers mixed with oleo.
Makes a crumbly crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bacon-hot dog appetizers
directions: Cut hot dots in fourths.
Cut bacon (1 strip) in thirds.
Wrap bacon around hot dogs.
Put toothpick to hold.
Sprinkle dark brown sugar over hot dogs.
Bake 40 minutes at 375°.

title: christmas morning sticky buns
directions: Sprinkle pecans in bottom of buttered 12 cup Bundt pan. Arrange dough in pan (I cut rolls in half), sprinkle with dry pudding mix.
Stir together melted margarine, brown sugar, cinnamon- pour over rolls.
Cover and chill for 8 hours.
Bake at 350 for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve immediately.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients and freeze.

title: cream cheese pie("makes own crust")
directions: Blend well the cheese, sugar, eggs (add one at a time).
Add almond extract and beat 5 minutes.
Butter generously a 9-inch pie plate; pour in pie plate and bake in 325° oven for 50 minutes. Cool 10 minutes.

title: three c cake
directions: Combine beaten eggs, oil, and milk in a large bowl.
Sift flour together with sugar, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt. Add egg mixture; mix well.
Stir in carrots, coconut, cherries, raisins and pecans.
Mix well.
Put in a large loaf pan.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: special recipe from south africa
directions: Combine patience, love and generosity with Understanding.
Add dash of Laughter and sprinkle with Kindness.
Add plenty of faith. Spread over a lifetime and serve everyone you meet.

title: no bake cookies (1)(peanut butter or chocolate)
directions: Mix sugar, oleo and milk (also cocoa, if using) together in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Boil for one minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop by tablespoon onto wax paper, cool, cookies harden fast so work quickly.	I have had this recipe from when I was in Middle school and have always used it.
(If you want to make the chocolate kind, use 2 Tbsp. cocoa, 4 Tbsp. oleo and 1 1/4 c. of oatmeal.
Rest of ingredients stay the same.)

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt.
Combine egg, water and vinegar and beat.
Pour liquid into flour mixture all at once. Blend with spoon until flour is moistened.
Can be kept in refrigerator or frozen up to 2 weeks.
Roll out on floured dough board.
Line pie plate and bake.

title: chinese almond cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Top each with a sliver of almond.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla. Pour into prepared pie crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Top with desired amount of pie filling before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: ham delights
directions: Cut the top off the rolls.
Spread over the bottoms of the rolls the mustard, butter, poppy seed and onions, then layer ham and cheese on onions.
Put top of roll back on.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: marie's chicken(yield:  4 - 6 servings)
directions: 1. Dredge chicken in flour.

title: cold relish
directions: Put in bowl.
Add 3 or 4 tablespoons salt.
Stir a few times and let sit 1/2 hour.
Drain.
Add 4 cups white sugar.
Add vinegar (enough to make juicy).
Add more sugar if you want to. Put in gallon jar in refrigerator to keep.

title: easter ham glaze
directions: Combine ingredients. Bring to a boil, then simmer. Spoon 1/2 cup on ham during last 30 minutes of baking. Heat remaining mixture and serve with sliced ham.

title: clam fritters with mustard sauce
directions: Heat oil (3 to 4 inches) in deep fat fryer to 375°.
Mix baking mix, cheese, onions, clams, reserved clam liquid, the egg and Worcestershire sauce just until blended.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown on all sides, 1 1/2 to 2 minutes; drain on paper towels.
Serve with Mustard Sauce.
Makes about 3 dozen appetizers.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain off all fat.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Simmer covered 10 to 15 minutes.
Layer like lasagna in 9 x 13-inch pan:
small amount of sauce on bottom of pan. Next, cut tortillas to make "noodle" layer.
Don't overlap. Layer of sauce mixture.
Layer of Cheddar.
Repeat tortillas and sauce.
Spread layer of sour cream before adding remaining Cheddar.
Cover and bake until hot at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Enjoy!

title: strawberry delight
directions: Slice berries and layer in dish.
Prepare jello as directed. Pour over berries and let set. Cut in squares and serve with reduced calorie Cool Whip. A sweet treat without the fat and calories!

title: peach cobbler
directions: Combine sugar and shortening. Add mixture of flour, baking powder and salt. Mix in milk and pour in a greased 9 x 13 baking dish. Pour peaches over top and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Note: Timing depends on size of dish.

title: banana muffins(fat-free)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray muffin cups with cooking spray. Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
In large bowl, beat egg whites lightly.
Stir in mashed bananas, milk and corn syrup.
Add flour mixture; stir until well blended.
Spoon into prepared muffin cups.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 5 minutes.

title: deer suckers
directions: Mix together, bring to a boil and then simmer for 15 minutes. Pour into a greased pan, put a piece of rope in one end of the pan, with about 2 feet of rope hanging outside of the pan. Sprinkle some shelled corn or oats into the mix and allow it to set up.
Hang in a tree and watch the deer have a ball.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in 3-quart baking dish, uncovered, for 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: crispy potato fingers
directions: Lightly grease shallow baking pan. Cut potatoes into 8 lengthwise wedges.
Brush with oil.
Place wedges spaced slightly apart in baking pan.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 35 minutes at 400°.
Serves 4.
Per serving: 4 wedges, 133 calories, 4 mg. sodium.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate raw potatoes.
Squeeze water out with towel.
Beat egg lightly and pour over potatoes.
Add flour.
Sprinkle spike over potatoes.
Heat vegetable oil until hot.
Drop potatoes by the spoonful into fat; brown lightly on each side.
Drain.
Serve with applesauce.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth; add green pepper, onion, pineapple, salt and 1 cup of pecans.
Mix well.
Cool until it can be rolled into a ball.
Roll in remaining nuts.
Chill at least 1 hour.
(Flavor increases if chilled overnight.)
Serve with crackers or party rye.

title: potato casserole
directions: Bake 1 hour at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: simmering sunday stew
directions: Spray casserole dish or grease.
Add beef; salt and pepper it to taste.
Add the Worcestershire and the dry onion soup mix. Cover and cook at 325° for 1 hour, then add vegetables.
Pour the beef broth over all and cook until vegetables and beef are tender. Beef could be put into crock-pot overnight and vegetables added in morning.

title: cheese cake bars
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and margarine together.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan or dish.

title: pat's irish cream nog
directions: Beat eggs until foamy at medium speed of an electric mixer. Gradually add sugar, beating 5 minutes or until thick and lemon colored.
Reduce speed to low; gradually add milk, liqueur and 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg, beating until combined.
Chill thoroughly.

title: low-fat brownies
directions: Mix together egg whites, nonfat milk, vanilla, fructose and applesauce.
Sift flour, baking powder and cocoa powder into liquid mixture and mix well.
Fold in chocolate chips and walnuts. Pour into an 8-inch pan, sprayed with nonstick spray.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Cool and cut into 16 bars.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and cream cheese together.
Add powdered sugar, then beat in Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Pour in graham cracker crust and refrigerate 2-3 hours before serving.

title: extra easy chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine pudding mix and milk in 1-quart glass bowl and cover.
Cook in microwave on High for 6 minutes.
Rotate and stir every 2 minutes or cook in saucepan on top of stove according to package directions.
Set aside, covered, and let cool for 10 to 15 minutes, then stir.

title: mushrooms in sour cream
directions: Wash mushrooms in cold water. Cut into thin pieces, slicing the mushroom along its length to preserve its form. Place butter in covered pan. Add mushrooms. Cook finely chopped onion until tender. Add onion to mushrooms. Salt and pepper to taste. Cook mushrooms until they are medium soft, at which point you reduce the heat to a very low level. Add beef stock, mixed with flour over very low heat until the consistency of gravy has been reached, add to mushrooms. Add sour cream and mix. Cook on low heat for 10 minutes.

title: beans and franks
directions: In a 2-quart casserole dish combine all ingredients.
Bake for 45 minutes at 400°, covered.
Then top with 1 package of wieners and bake uncovered for 15 minutes more.

title: cherry delight
directions: Crust:
Mix graham cracker crumbs and melted margarine together.
Press in 9 x 13 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Chill.

title: portuguese corn bread(pao de milko)
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water and 1 teaspoon of sugar.
Let stand 5 minutes until double.
Place flour in large bowl.
Add yeast and 2 cups of warm water.
Mix and knead for 5 minutes.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk.
Bring 2 cups of water and salt to a boil.
Pour boiling water over corn meal flour. Mix very fast.
Cool.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown beef in 4 or 5-quart pan; drain off fat.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bring to boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Mix cream cheese and bacon together. Hollow out the portabella mushrooms a little and wipe them off with a wet paper towel; don't wash under water. Stuff the mixture into the mushrooms. Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Halve and seed peppers. Boil peppers 3 minutes. Drain. Brown hamburger, drain off fat. Mix hamburger with all other ingredients, except green peppers. Fill pepper halves with meat mix. Refrigerate or freeze. Heat before serving.

title: homemade reese's candy
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well.
Roll into balls and place on wax paper.
Melt chocolate and wax (paraffin) together in saucepan.
Dip balls in chocolate mixture and place back on wax paper to cool.

title: ice cream custard
directions: When in freezer, add can of condensed milk and fill with regular milk.

title: shoe peg corn salad
directions: Drain vegetables and mix in bowl.
Add green pepper, onion, celery and pimentos.
In saucepan, mix sugar, salt, vinegar, pepper and oil.
Heat to boiling but do not boil.
Cool, then add to vegetables and refrigerate.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Scald milk; melt the chocolate in the milk and then add the sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Cook until thick.
Beat the egg yolks and add a small amount of the chocolate mixture to them; stir. Add to the hot mixture.
Cook a few minutes longer, stirring every few minutes.
Continue until mix is thick.
Add butter and vanilla; let cool.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with whatever you choose.
This is for a large pie shell!

title: cube steak casserole
directions: Slice onions lengthwise and saute in margarine.
Do not brown. Remove onions from pan and brown cube steak.
Layer in casserole dish soup, onions and steak.
Continue until all ingredients are used, ending with soup.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: 24 hour veg salad
directions: Place 2 cups of lettuce in the bottom of a large bowl; sprinkle with salt, pepper and sugar.
Layer eggs atop lettuce in bowl.
Sprinkle with more salt.
Layer in order:
peas, remaining lettuce, bacon and Swiss cheese.
Spread mayonnaise over top, sealing to edge of bowl.
Cover and chill 24 hours.
Garnish with green onion and paprika.
Toss before serving.
This recipe makes 12 to 15 servings, and is great for making ahead when you're expecting guests the following day.

title: apple raisin bread
directions: Grease two 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pans.
In medium bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, cinnamon and ginger.
In large bowl, with mixer at medium speed, beat together oleo and sugar. Beat in syrup.
Add eggs and beat until well mixed.
With wooden spoon, stir in apples.
Stir in flour mixture, raisins and nuts. Divide into 2 pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: tomato relish
directions: Combine all ingredients together; cook until done.
Makes 4 pints.

title: mini cheese cakes
directions: Line cupcake pan with paper liners.
Put vanilla wafer in bottom of each one.
Mix all ingredients until very smooth.
Pour batter on wafers.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Serve cold with any toppings.

title: haystacks(candy)
directions: Melt morsels.
Mix all ingredients together and shape by dropping teaspoon size balls on wax paper.
Let cool.

title: mother's cereal mix
directions: Melt together fat and oleo and add sugar, salt and sauce. Pour over cereal.
Mix.
Bake 1 hour at 200°.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: christmas punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in large container.
Stir until sugar is completely melted.
Place in freezable containers.
Add 1 bottle ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: snicker bar cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, brown sugar, butter, and peanut butter. Add vanilla and beaten eggs, mix.
Add soda, baking powder, and flour, mix well.
Cut miniature snickers in half of candy bars forming a ball.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Drain and save pineapple juice.
Mix juice, brown sugar, soy sauce and garlic powder thoroughly.
Add chicken breasts one at a time.
Top with pineapple slices.
Soak for at least 12 hours. Cook 10 minutes each side on grill at medium to low.
Add more pineapple juice if meat is not mostly covered with marinade.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Put in sauce pan; 1 c sugar, 3 tbsp cocoa, 3 rounded tbsp flour. Add in center, 3 egg yolks and start blending gradually. Add 1 c pet milk, mix well. Place
over hot heat and stir constantly until thick. Add 1 tsp vanilla, 1 tbsp milk and butter. Put in baked pastry shell and top with meringue.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Place popcorn into 2 large mixing bowls.
Mix sugar, butter, syrups and salt in a medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil and let boil 5 minutes on medium heat.
Stir in vanilla and soda.
Mix well.
Slowly pour over popcorn.
Stir in well.
Drop into a greased jelly roll pan.
Bake 1 hour at 250°.
Don't stir.
Store in an airtight bowl.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Line casserole dish with Doritos, bottom and sides.
Start with mixture of canned things.
Layer chicken, canned mixture and cheese (save enough cheese to cover for last 10 minutes of baking).
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Add rest of cheese on top and bake for 10 minutes.
Entire dish is better if chilled overnight before baking.

title: pecan pie mini muffins
directions: Combine brown sugar, flour and pecans. Set aside. Combine butter and eggs; mix well. Stir in flour mixture just until moistened. Fill greased and floured mini muffin pan until 2/3 full. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until muffins test done. Remove immediately to cool on wire rack. Yield: about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use 3 tablespoons of mix to 8 ounces of hot water.
Delicious.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute the first 4 ingredients in pan. In large bowl, combine tomatoes, rice, cheese and seasonings. Remove casing on sausage and break apart; cook down. Cool and add to vegetables. Put all into greased casserole. Spread 1 cup shredded cheese on top. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove cover and bake 5 minutes more.
Make a salad and enjoy!

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pistachio pudding (right out of the box, unprepared) and pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add fruit cocktail and mandarin oranges.
Top with cherries.

title: baba cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until light (5 minutes).
Add salt, milk, flour, baking powder and mace.
Mix together with melted butter; mix well.
Bake in Bundt pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: french toast chicken sandwich
directions: Purchase loaf of French bread.
Slice in 12 equal pieces. Spread each piece with equal parts of garlic spread & butter or margarine.
Wrap bread in aluminum foil & place in oven at 325 for approx. 15-20 minutes.
Enjoy!!

title: hard candy
directions: Boil, without stirring, to 265° and then add coloring. Continue boiling to 290° and add flavoring.
Remove at 300° from fire and pour onto greased marble slab or metal tray.
Mark with knife and break apart with scissors when workable.
Makes 2 1/2 pounds.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream, cream cheese and taco mix with electric mixer. Spread into pie dish; cover and chill overnight.
Layer lettuce, tomatoes, cheese and taco sauce.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, buttermilk, butter, and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in coconut.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° until golden brown.
Approximately 45 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Prepare cookie mix and put on 12-inch pizza pan. Bake at 475° for 10 minutes. Cool.
Blend cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Spread on crust.
Arrange fruit on top.
Top with cooled glaze.

title: washugal
directions: Stir-fry kielbasa in skillet with a little oil on high. Peel potatoes and shred them. Add them to kielbasa and lower heat to medium. Cover skillet and cook about ten minutes. Flip mixture over and cook for 4-5 minutes. Take 6 eggs and mix up in bowl. Pour over potato and kielbasa mixture. Then cook the mixture like scrambled eggs. Use shredded cheese to sprinkle over mixture (I use Cheddar cheese). Put lid back on until cheese is melted.

title: baked stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells as directed.
Prepare your own spaghetti sauce or use jar sauce.
In large bowl, combine Ricotta cheese, sharp cheese, Parmesan cheese, basil, oregano and pepper.
Mix well. Fill each shell with plenty of mixture.

title: baker's original german sweet chocolate cake
directions: *Or 2 1/2 cups sifted cake flour.

title: punch
directions: Mix strawberries and sherbet lightly and before serving.
Add ginger ale.

title: seafood linguine
directions: Saute garlic and parsley, that have been finely chopped, in olive oil in a large frying pan over low heat.
Clean and devein shrimp.
Add crabmeat, shrimp and scallops to olive oil; saute until shrimp and scallops are no longer translucent, approximately 10 to 15 minutes.
Cook linguine as per instructions on box.
Add 1 tablespoon olive oil to water as the noodles will not stick to each other.
Drain and rinse noodles to serve.
Place linguine on plate and spoon seafood on top.
May also be served chilled.

title: rosemary tea
directions: Grind tea and rosemary in a blender or food processor.
Store in airtight container.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a 2-quart glass mixing bowl (I like the big measuring bowl with a handle), stir together sugar, syrup, peanuts and salt. Mix well.
Microwave on High for 6 to 9 minutes until light brown. Add vanilla and butter.
Microwave on High for 1 or 2 minutes. Peanuts should be light brown and the syrup at the hard crack stage.
Add baking soda.
Stir until light and foamy.
Pour on lightly buttered cookie sheet.
Let cool at least 1/2 hour before breaking into pieces.
Keeps a long time in tightly closed container.

title: corned beef appetiziers
directions: Spread either margarine or mustard on one side of tortilla. Place several slices corned beef on top, covering entire tortilla surface.
Roll up.
Place toothpicks in roll, 1-inch apart.
Slice between toothpicks.
Serve chilled.

title: tang pie
directions: Mix Tang and milk together, then add the rest of the ingredients. Makes 2 pies.

title: six weeks bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients. Stir well.
Bake in muffin tins 18 to 20 minutes at 400°.
Will keep up to 6 weeks in refrigerator.
Take out and bake as you want.

title: cabbage roll casserole
directions: In a greased casserole dish or 9 x 13-inch pan, place 1/2 the chopped cabbage.
Combine meat, rice, salt, garlic powder, sour cream and onion.
Form into patties and place over cabbage.
Add rest of cabbage over the top.
Then sprinkle with cheese to cover entire casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: enchiladas
directions: Fry ground meat in skillet until brown.
Add onions and cook until tender.
Drain and set aside.
Heat enchilada sauce until hot.
Fry tortillas in hot grease, about 1 minute, each side. Then dip in enchilada sauce and put in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. Layer 6 tortillas, meat, sauce and cheese.
Make 2 layers using all meat and sauce.
Top with lots of cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° until all cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: refrigerator potato rolls
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water to cover until tender.
Drain potatoes, reserving 1 cup liquid.
(Add water to equal 1 cup if necessary.)
Set potato water aside.
Mash potatoes.
Set aside. Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In a large bowl, combine ingredients in order given.
Pour into prepared pan.
Cut in squares while still hot.
Cool completely. Watch out, they disappear fast!

title: grandma's molasses cookies
directions: Mix sugar, Crisco and eggs.
Add molasses and coffee.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Chill.
Roll and bake in 375° oven.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix well.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: "dirt" cake
directions: You will need a flowerpot, artificial flowers, a toy spade, etc.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in loaf pan. Drain.
Bake 10 minutes more.

title: apple muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add combined milk, egg and oil. Stir just until moistened. Add apples. Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: marinated carrot salad
directions: Boil sliced carrots in a small amount of unsalted water until tender, but crisp.
Combine ingredients for the sauce and mix well.
Add the green pepper and onions.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over carrots.
Refrigerate for 48 hours before serving.

title: swedish almond toast(cookie)
directions: Cream the butter and sugar well; add eggs. Add the other ingredients, alternating sour cream and flour last.
Bake in 3 greased bread pans at 325° for 55 minutes. Cool.
Wrap in foil and put in freezer overnight.
(Do not omit this step.)
Remove from freezer and let stand at room temperature until loaves can be sliced. Slice 1/4-inch thick.
Place slices on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 250°, turning slices every 10 to 15 minutes, until lightly browned (takes about 1 hour).
Let dry thoroughly before storing.
Store in a cool, dry place.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
Stir in flour, sugar and milk. Add blackberries.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quick and easy casserole
directions: Put ground beef in bottom of an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Spread soup over meat.
Put potatoes on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chili con carne
directions: Heat oil in skillet; saute onions, garlic and green peppers until onions become translucent.
Add ground beef and brown.
In large pot, combine remaining ingredients.
Mix in ground beef mixture.
Cover and simmer for 2 to 3 hours.
Store overnight; reheat to ripen and blend flavors.

title: corn casserole (3)
directions: Saute green pepper & onion in 1 Tbsp. butter over low heat. Remove from heat. In medium bowl, combine all ingredients together until well blended. Turn into baking dish and bake at 375° for 50-60 minutes.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Heat oil in pan.
Saute diced onion.
When onion is browned, add crushed tomatoes.
Let cook for 1/2 hour.
Add tomato sauce and paste.
Add 2 cups of water and spices.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.

title: potato soup with butter dumplings
directions: Saute onion in 1/4 cup butter in large saucepan until tender. Add water.
Bring to a boil.
Add potatoes, celery, salt to taste, pepper and parsley.
Reduce heat.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients in large salad bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and cheese.
Spread over other ingredients.
Sprinkle with bacon bits if desired.
Refrigerate overnight and toss before serving.

title: marinated sliced tomatoes
directions: Wash, dry and slice tomatoes thick.
Arrange on platter or in shallow dish slightly overlapping.
Mix remaining ingredients. Drizzle over tomatoes.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Garnish with parsley and serve.
Serves 4.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Mix the cheese until well blended.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Shape into two balls. Roll in finely chopped pecans, if desired.

title: harvest sweet potato pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine first 10 ingredients.
Mix well. Beat in sweet potatoes; pour into pie shells.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes longer. Cool completely.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: chicken bits
directions: Egg and bread chicken pieces.
Fry until brown and drain. Place in a baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese over chicken and cover with the soup and wine.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes. Yields 4 servings.
Recipe can be multiplied for larger portions.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and carrots.
In bowl, mix together mayonnaise, vinegar, milk, sugar and mustard until smooth.
Mix with cabbage and carrots.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix cookie dough according to package.
Pat dough out into round pizza pan (greased).
Bake until edges are crispy and golden.
Cool completely.
Mix softened cream cheese and Cool Whip together.
Spread mixture on cooled crust.
Arrange fruit on top of Cool Whip mixture.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: orange salad
directions: Reserve 1 cup pineapple and oranges.
Bring to a boil and combine with orange gelatin.
Chill until partially set.
Fold all remaining ingredients into partially set gelatin.
Refrigerate until firm.
Serve.

title: chicken broccoli potato and cheese soup
directions: Peel and dice the potatoes.
chop the broccoli.
Boil the potatoes for 30 minutes and drain.
Cook chicken in microwave till done.
Save juice.
Add chicken and juice, broccoli, broth and butter to potatoes and bring to a slow boil for 15 minutes.

title: homemade kahlua
directions: Bring water, sugar and coffee to boiling; cool.
Add 1/5 bottle grain alcohol.
Add vanilla.
Bottle.
This is the normal recipe.

title: oven parmesan chips
directions: Cut potatoes into 1/4-inch slices.
Place on a greased baking sheet in a single layer.
Mix butter, salt, onion, pepper and paprika.
(Brush on both sides of potatoes.) Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Serve immediately.

title: peanut butter fudge(microwave)
directions: Heat 2 minutes on High.
Add vanilla to taste.
Blend well and pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.

title: ham-cheese souffle sandwiches
directions: Lay 6 slices bread in casserole.
Spread ham evenly over bread. Place 6 slices bread on top of ham.
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until solid.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Combine egg whites, syrup, sugar and salt in upper part of double boiler.
Beat with rotary beater until partially mixed. Set pan over rapidly boiling water.
Cook 7 minutes, beating constantly, with a rotary beater until frosting stand in peaks. Remove pan from hot water.
Add flavoring.
Beat into mix well. Makes enough to cover top and sides of 2 round 8 or 9-inch layers.

title: quick sunday sweet rolls
directions: Bake spiraled rolls until lightly browned.
Remove from oven and brush with butter.
Combine sugar and cinnamon to make cinnamon-sugar in a bowl.
Dip buttered rolls in sugar, coating top and bottom.
Delicious warm.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix together sour cream, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing. Crumble cornbread in a baking dish (8 x 10-inch).
Add the other ingredients in the order listed.
Sprinkle bacon bits over top.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown beef, garlic and onion.
Drain grease if necessary.
Add salt, pepper, flour, soup and sour cream.
Mix. Heat through and serve over, hot cooked noodles immediately.

title: creamed spinach casserole
directions: Use microwave. Spray 2-quart casserole with Pam. Add spinach and cook according to package directions. Add butter, sliced in pieces, heat and melt. Add cream cheese; heat and stir. Add mushrooms and bacon; heat and stir. Season to taste.

title: easy jello
directions: Mix all dry ingredients and add the boiling water, cold water and whipping cream. Pour all ingredients into a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Whipping cream will eventually rise to top.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Put in a 2-quart casserole dish (ungreased).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Fry hamburg and some onions until brown.
Season your hamburg. In a casserole, put a layer of noodles, then the remaining ingredients.
Add rest of noodles and meat on top.
Mix together slightly.
Put 1/2 pound Velveeta cheese on top.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: overnight casserole
directions: In large bowl, combine milk and soup; mix until smooth.
Add uncooked macaroni, water chestnuts, chicken, onion, cheese, 3 hard-cooked eggs and salt. Mix well and refrigerate overnight tightly covered.

title: blueberry brunch cake
directions: Combine first four ingredients in medium bowl, set aside. Combine egg, milk, oil and lemon juice; add to dry ingredients. Mix well.
Pour batter into a greased 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with blueberries.
Combine remaining, sprinkle over blueberries. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding tomatoes last.
It will be chunky. Retain avocado seeds and put in dip to keep from turning brown. Serve with tortilla chips; the lime 'n chile ones are really good.

title: deep chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 12-cup Bundt pan.
In medium bowl, combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
In separate bowl, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat in vanilla, then flour mixture in at 3 parts at a time, alternating in the sour cream.
Bake 45 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Sprinkle the powdered sugar over top.

title: mexican mole dinner
directions: Simmer chicken until tender.
Cool in broth.
Skin, bone and cut in small pieces.
Heat bacon drippings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Note:
Can use 3 cans biscuits and raisins can be used.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Mix 1 1/4 cups sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan.
Stir in water, vinegar, and butter.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Remove from heat.
In a small dish, beat egg yolks into a small amount of mixture, then add this back to the saucepan.
Return to heat and cook 3 minutes more.
Pour into the pie shell.
Cool.
In a medium bowl, beat egg whites with cream of tartar; gradually add the other 1/4 cup sugar.
Beat until stiff. Spread over pie and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: orange pineapple salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple.
Add all ingredients and chill.

title: snowballs
directions: Put the coconut and sprinkles in a square baking pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Mix them together.
With an ice cream scoop, make 4 balls of ice cream.
Place the balls in the baking pan.
Using 2 spoons, roll the balls around until each one is coated with the coconut mixture.
Lift each ball out of the pan with the spoon and into a dessert dish.
Put the dishes in the freezer for 10 minutes so that the ice cream can get good and hard again.

title: dressing for wild turkey
directions: Mix and rub on turkey.
Let set for short time.
Roast, covered, for 12 hours at 250° for about 13 to 15 pound turkey.

title: danish holiday pastry
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Measure first cup of flour into bowl.
Cut in 1/2 cup butter.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons water and mix with fork.
Round into ball and divide in half.
Pat dough with hands into 2 long strips 12 x 3 inches.
Strips should be 3 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Mix the second amount of butter (1/2 cup) and water in saucepan.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Add almond flavoring and remove from heat.
Stir in flour immediately to keep it from lumping.
When smooth and thick, add 1 egg at at time, beating until smooth.
Divide in half and spread 1/2 evenly over each piece of pastry.
Bake about 50 minutes until topping is nicely browned.
Frost with powdered sugar icing and decorate with slivered almonds and candied cherries.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Top with herb stuffing.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; chill or freeze.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Mix chicken, soup and sour cream.
Pour into baking dish.
Dot with margarine, crumble crackers on top and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until bubbly.

title: butterscotch yule log
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels over hot water (not boiling). Remove from heat; stir in condensed milk and vanilla.
Add chopped pecans and mix well.
Chill until firm enough to handle.

title: overnight cauliflower salad
directions: In a medium size bowl, place lettuce, then cauliflower and onion and top with as much bacon bits as you like.
Combine mayonnaise and sugar.
Drop by spoonfuls over top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
When ready to serve, stir thoroughly.

title: striped delight
directions: Combine graham crackers, sugar and melted butter.
Press firmly in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and 2 tablespoons milk until smooth.
Fold in half of Cool Whip. Spread over crust.
Prepare instant pudding with 3 1/2 cups milk. Pour over cream cheese layer.
Chill several hours or overnight. Spread remaining Cool Whip over pudding.

title: spicy pecan muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 medium muffin cups (2 1/2 x 1 1/4 inches).
Mix all ingredients, except 2 teaspoons sugar; beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Divide batter evenly among cups (about 2/3 full).
Sprinkle with 2 teaspoons sugar.
Bake for about 15 minutes, or until golden brown.
Immediately remove from pan. Serve warm.
Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: nan's company casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet, then add onion, green pepper and salt. When done, add spaghetti, all soups, water and mushrooms.
Place in a 3-quart casserole which has been buttered.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Put popcorn in a large brown grocery bag.
In microwave bowl, combine sugar, oleo and syrup.
Mix and bring to a boil on High. Stir only once; then microwave 2 minutes more.
Add baking soda to mixture in bowl.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla flavoring.
Mix until it foams up to double
in size.
Pour over corn and mix well.
Place bag in microwave for 2 minutes.
Stir well.
Microwave 2 minutes more.
Stir well.
Then 1 minute.
Pour out of bag and cool.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix the soup, sour cream and Ro-Tel in a bowl.
Set aside. In a 9 x 13-inch pan, make 3 layers of chips, onions, cheese, chicken and soup mixture.
Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: atjar cabbage
directions: Mix all vegetables together in a bowl.
Combine lemon juice, red pepper, salt and sugar; pour dressing over the vegetables and mix well.
Marinate for at least 1 hour.

title: chesapeake chicken
directions: In a large baking dish, put in soups.
Add 1 1/2 cans water and rice.
Stir and mix well.
Add onion soup mix and stir.
Lay in pieces of chicken on top.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: classic pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour on a hot pancake griddle. Cook until batter starts to dry around the edges and flip.

title: bill's chess pie
directions: Melt butter.
Mix together sugar, vinegar, cornmeal and eggs. Mix well.
Pour into pastry-lined pie plate.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°, then 40 minutes at 250°.

title: ham and swiss delights
directions: Melt butter, add onion powder and poppy seed.
Split roll, add ham and cheese.
Cover roll with melted butter, onion powder and poppy seed mixture.
You may freeze and take out one as needed or use immediately by baking for 5 minutes at 350°.

title: black magic cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Bake at 350° in loaf pan for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Fry onion and beef.
Drain as needed.
Add beans, tomato, chilies and picante sauce.
Keep liquid to a minimum.
Stir while heating to warm.
Place in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan or serving dish.
Cover mixture with sour cream.
Layer cheeses on top to cover.
Bake until hot and cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: bran loaf
directions: Soak all ingredients overnight.
Add one cup self-rising flour and bake in loaf pan at 350°
for 1 hour.
Serve.
Spread with butter.

title: creamed chicken
directions: In a heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt the butter.
Add green pepper.
Cook gently about 5 minutes.
Stir in flour.
Add chicken stock and milk.
Cook and stir constantly until boiling and thickened.
Remove from heat.
Mix a little of the sauce with the egg yolks.
Stir back into remaining sauce.
Stir in sherry, nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Return to low heat and cook and stir for a few minutes.
Add chicken, pimento and cream of chicken soup. Reheat gently.
Serve in tart or patty shells.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: cheese dip
directions: Slice olives and place all ingredients in glass dish. Microwave for 5 to 10 minutes or bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel the cucumbers.
Put in blender with a little water. Blend. Drain on paper towel in colander.
Mix all ingredients, pour in a 5-cup mold and chill.

title: spicy rice
directions: Saute onions and peppers in butter in large skillet for approximately 3
minutes.
Add
rice
and
stir
well
for one minute.
Add chicken broth and corn.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer to desired consistency.

title: cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Microwave tortillas until soft (45 seconds).
Fry onion, thinly sliced, in 2 tablespoons butter until almost brown.
Remove from heat; add chicken, pimentos, peppers, cream cheese and sour cream.
Toss lightly; season with salt.

title: stuffed pepper casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and bell pepper.
Drain.
Add stewed tomatoes and rice.
Season to taste with chili powder, salt and pepper.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: paper bag apple pie
directions: Place sliced, peeled and cored apples in large bowl.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and nutmeg; sprinkle over apples.
Toss to coat well.
Place in pie shell.
Drizzle apple mixture with lemon juice.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup flour in bowl (for topping).
Cut in butter and sprinkle evenly over apples.
Slide pie into heavy brown paper bag.
Fold end and fasten with paper clips or staples.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 1 hour.
Split bag open, remove and cool.
All the mess is in the bag!

title: kool-aid play dough
directions: Put ingredients in a saucepan.
Cook at medium temperature, stirring constantly, until mixture becomes dough-like and pulls away from the pan.
Remove from pan and cool.
Store in an airtight container.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Fix pudding as directed.
Crush up Oreo cookies.
Place half of cookies on bottom of pan.
Mix pudding, cream cheese, butter, sugar and Cool Whip.
Place mixture over Oreos, then spread the rest of Oreo cookies on top of mixture.

title: gayle's picante sauce
directions: Chop tomatoes, garlic, onions and peppers.
Add tomato sauce, sugar and garlic salt.
Simmer for 30 to 45 minutes, until thick. May add some of the juice of the tomatoes, if needed.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Mix well and place in baking dish.

title: aquarium gelatin
directions: Make gelatin according to package directions.
When it is slightly cooked, divide it among 6 plastic cups.
When gelatin is partially set, add three or more gummy fish to each cup.
Place cups in refrigerator for 2 hours.
At serving time top with cool whip to form "surf".
Top with fish crackers (optional).

title: fajita marinade and baste
directions: Combine
all ingredients in a large saucepan.
Bring to a full boil.	Remove from heat; cool down.
Keep refrigerated until needed.
Serves 25.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Beat eggs and add onions, pour into a frying pan and cool. Stir until eggs are almost done.
Add potatoes and sausage and cook until all are done.
Put 3/4 cup of mixture on floured tortilla shell and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with grated cheese, cover and bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Serve with salsa.

title: microwave beef and bean tacos
directions: Crumble ground beef into a 2-quart casserole dish; add onion. Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High for 3 to 5 minutes, until meat loses pink color, stirring after 2 minutes.
Drain; stir in pork and beans, taco sauce and chili powder.
Cover; microwave on High 5 to 7 minutes, until heated through, stirring after 3 minutes.
Put meat mixture in taco shells and top with lettuce, tomato, cheese and sour cream.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain and set aside.
Melt oleo. Add flour and saute briefly.
Add half and half.
Mix chicken broth with hot water and add to flour mixture, stirring until well blended.
Add broccoli to sauce and add salt and pepper to taste.

title: date-nut cookies
directions: Put chopped dates into 1 cup of boiling water.
Add 1 teaspoon baking soda and let stand while you mix the following: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients and date mixture. Stir and put into greased cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 15 - 20 minutes.
Frost with butter frosting.
Cut into diamond shapes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine cans of any favorite fruits (peach slices, fruit cocktail, mandarin oranges or pineapple chunks).
Add your choice of other ingredients (marshmallows, etc.).
Stir in box of pudding mix.
Let stand for a few minutes to thicken; serve.

title: spicy hot potato salad
directions: Toss ingredients and marinate for at least one hour.
If salad is too dry, add Italian dressing.

title: baked brisket
directions: Add small amount (enough to make a paste) of water.
Mix all ingredients together (except the meat) to make a thick paste.
Pat the mix over all sides of meat.
Wrap in foil once, then wrap again in heavy foil.
Be sure to seal the foil well each time. This may be done the day before use or it may be frozen.
Thaw before cooking.
On day it is to be eaten, bake in 325° oven for 3 hours.
Allow to rest 10 to 15 minutes before slicing in thin slices (across the grain of meat).
Serve with the juices from the meat.
Serves 6 to 10.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add vanilla wafer crumbs and milk.
Fold in pecans and coconut.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan or bundt pan. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 275 degrees.

title: banana bread(ultra low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl and mix well.
Bake in loaf pan sprayed with nonstick cooking spray at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Recipe makes 10 servings.

title: marshmallow pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, gelatin, brown sugar, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, ginger, egg yolks and milk. Cook over medium heat until mixture boils. Cool. Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry. Gradually add sugar while continuing to beat. Fold into the pumpkin mixture with marshmallows. Pour into baked pie shell and chill.

title: peanut butter butter balls
directions: You also need 2 cookie sheets and about 50 mini muffin cups.

title: magic muffins
directions: Combine ingredients and stir until flour is moistened.
Fill greased muffin cups or use paper baking cups 3/4 full.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: good sandwich spread
directions: Grind red peppers, green peppers and onions.
Drain off water. Add sugar, salt, mustard, vinegar, mayonnaise and flour.
Boil 5 minutes or until thick.
Seal.
Makes 5 pints.

title: diabetic banana pudding
directions: Layer vanilla wafers and bananas.
Combine all other ingredients in top of double boiler.
Cook until thick.
Pour over bananas and wafers.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple and blueberries--reserve juice.
Add water to reserved juice to make 4 cups.
Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add juice/water mixture to jello.
Reserve 2 cups jello mixture for topping.
Add pineapple and blueberries to remaining jello.
Chill until firm.
Prepare dream whip according to package directions. Chill remaining jello until egg white consistency.
Combine this with dream whip and nuts.
Spread over firm jello.
Serves:

title: skillet baked beans
directions: Chop the onion fine and saute with bacon. Add pork and beans, brown sugar, catsup, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Stir now and then while continuing to simmer.
Cook 45 minutes over charcoal coals or turn out into casserole and bake indoors 45 minutes at 350°.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar, syrup, salt, vanilla and butter.
Beat well, then add pecans. Put in unbaked pie shell. Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
If using deep dish pie shell, will make one.

title: cornbread skillet casserole
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients in a bowl.
Set aside.
Cook the ground beef until brown; drain.
Pour half of the cornmeal mixture into a greased 10 1/2-inch cast-iron skillet. Sprinkle evenly with beef (or crawfish). Top with cheese, onion and peppers.
Pour remaining batter over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Boil first 5 ingredients until thick and pour into baked pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip. Can be cooked in microwave.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all these ingredients together.
Then put Cool Whip in the mixture and mix well.
Put in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: peter pan choco surprises
directions: Cream the peanut butter, margarine and brown sugar.
Add eggs. Mix in dry ingredients.
Wrap 1 teaspoon of dough around each chocolate piece.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: polish drumstick torte
directions: Mix and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 300°.
Cool.

title: mom's quick spaghetti
directions: Fill large pot with water and oil.
Bring to a boil.
Put meat in skillet and brown.
When 1/2 done, cover in garlic powder. Put onion with meat.
Drain and put back in skillet on medium heat.
Add tomato sauce, golden mushroom soup and mushrooms until it bubbles while stirring.
Turn to low heat and add cheese.
When it melts, it's done.
When water boils, put spaghetti in.
When you throw it against the wall and it sticks, it's done.
If you think sauce is too thick, add tomato juice.

title: cabbage and bow tie pasta
directions: Cook bow tie pasta until tender.
Saute onions and cabbage in butter until tender.
Combine drained pasta and vegetables. Serves 8 to 10.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Mix and shape into balls the size of walnuts.
Place in a flat pan in a single layer.

title: beef and cheese casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Brown meat, break up with fork and stir in garlic powder (optional). Add tomato sauce and simmer over low heat.

title: beef, beans and more
directions: Brown ground chuck, ground turkey and onion together in a Dutch oven. Drain. Add other ingredients and stir well. Add 1 to 2 soup cans of water, depending on desired consistency. Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 25 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve hot with rice.

title: shrimp fettucine
directions: Saute onions, celery and bell pepper in butter.
Add in other ingredients.
Place in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, syrup and salt.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add soda.
Stir.
(It foams.)
Pour over a large bowl of popped corn.

title: cukes for kids
directions: Place cucumbers in a strainer.
Sprinkle with salt; let stand for 30 minutes, tossing occasionally.
Rinse and drain well.
In a bowl, combine the oil, vinegar, sugar and pepper; add the cucumbers and stir well.
Sprinkle with onions and paprika. Refrigerate until serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fresh banana cooler
directions: Place bananas, honey and a small amount of milk in blender. Puree until smooth.
Add remaining milk and ice cream.
Blend until smooth and frothy.
Serve with banana slices on top.
Makes approximately 4 large glasses.

title: green tomato and apple pie
directions: Green tomatoes lend this pie a very distinctive flavor.
I find that weighing the flour makes this more accurate.

title: apple crisp
directions: Prepare 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan by greasing well with butter. Arrange sliced apples in bottom of pan.
Pour 1/4 cup water and 1 tablespoon lemon juice over apples.
Blend together 1 cup sugar, 1/2 cup sifted flour, 1/4 cup butter and 1 teaspoon cinnamon. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with cream.

title: kielbasa-rice bake
directions: Place the ingredients in a greased casserole and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix at low speed 1 minute. Then 2 minutes at medium speed. Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes. Cool 10 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix boiling water and oatmeal; let stand.
Blend white and brown sugars with eggs.
Add remaining ingredients; stir in oatmeal.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cajun roast
directions: Poke holes in the roast. In each hole put 1 pepper, and a pinch of garlic. Put as many holes as you desire. Sprinkle black pepper over the top of the roast. Place in cooking bag. Cook until done.

title: blueberry-cheese muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In mixing bowl, combine butter, brown sugar and eggs.
Beat with electric mixer until light and fluffy.
On a piece of waxed paper, sift together 2 3/4 cups flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
In a small bowl, blend milk, sour cream, cheese and vanilla.
Alternately add flour and milk mixtures to butter mixture.
Blend thoroughly.
Rinse and drain berries and combine with remaining 1/4 cup flour; toss gently.
Carefully fold berries into batter.
Mix cinnamon and sugar together.
Line muffin tins and spoon into cups 3/4 full.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all and pour into shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bud's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in pan and bring to boil.
Cool and dilute with water to taste.

title: hamburger scramble
directions: Spray casserole with Pam.
Crumble hamburger in casserole dish.
Add chopped onion and green pepper. Cover with the Cheddar cheese soup, then top with Tater Tots. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until Tots are brown and crispy.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan also.

title: meringue shells
directions: For a single large shell, lightly oil a 9-inch pie pan.
For small individual meringues, place unglazed brown paper on cookie sheet.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until foamy.
Beat until peaks form. Gradually add sugar and vanilla.
Beat 1 minute more.

Spread the meringue in pie pan, building up the sides to be thicker than the bottom or shape into 12 x 4-inch diameter shells, making impressions in the middle with back of spoon. Bake at 275° for 1 hour and 15 minutes (until dry and light creamy color). Let cool. Remove carefully. Meringues may be stored in an airtight container until ready to fill.
Fill with lite cherry pie filling or diet instant pudding and sliced banana.
Contains 60 calories per serving.

title: pork chop and rice casserole
directions: Grease a casserole.
Place uncooked rice in bottom of casserole.
Sprinkle onion and green pepper over top.
Place pork chops on top.
In separate bowl, mix soup and water together and pour over top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Marinate tri tips 3 days.
Great for barbecue, cook until desired doneness.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine ingredients and beat thoroughly with a rotary beater or electric mixer.
Keep refrigerated.
Shake well before each using; makes 1 1/2 pints.

title: pecan-sweet potato crunch
directions: Sprinkle on mixture and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fat-free coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, mix all ingredients, one at a time, stirring well after each addition. Pour batter into a round 9-inch nonstick cake pan that's been lightly coated with cooking spray and dusted with flour.

title: munchie oyster crackers
directions: In a large mixing bowl, sprinkle oil over crackers, then add dry salad mixture, coating crackers to taste.
Enjoy!!

title: onion soup meat loaf
directions: Shape into loaf pan and bake at 350° for about 1 1/4 hours.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Remove from cookie sheet carefully with spatula because cookies will be very soft. For more cookies, double or triple recipe.

title: breakfast haystack
directions: Enough for 30 people.

title: barbecued burgers
directions: Preheat an outdoor grill for high heat, and lightly oil grate.
In a large bowl, mix ground beef, egg, quick cooking oats, dried onion flakes, seasoning salt, pepper, ketchup, and dry onion soup mix.
Form the mixture into about 4 burger patties.
Place burger patties on the prepared grill, and cook about 5 minutes on each side, to an internal temperature of 160°.

title: 24 stuffed finger rolls
directions: Brown the beef, garlic, onion and salt and pepper in a large skillet.
Add tomato sauce, eggs and cheese.
Stir until thickened.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour in baking dish and cook about 50 minutes (or until done) at 250°.

title: chicken reuben
directions: In a 3-quart baking dish, spoon Thousand Island dressing to cover bottom of dish.
Arrange chicken breasts in serving sized pieces.
Place drained sauerkraut on top of chicken.
Arrange Swiss cheese slices on top of sauerkraut.
Lastly, pour the entire bottle of dressing over all.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: chicken with raspberry vinegar
directions: Place each chicken breast half between 2 pieces of clear plastic wrap; pound to 1/8-inch thickness.
In heavy skillet, melt 1 tablespoon of butter until sizzling.
Add chicken breasts; cook on each side about 2 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink. Transfer to heated platter.
Add remaining 1 tablespoon butter, onion and mushrooms to skillet.
Cook, stirring constantly, about 1 minute.
Stir in vinegar, brown sugar and soy sauce.
Heat until blended and bubbly.
Add sour cream; stir until well blended and heated through.
Pour over chicken breasts.
Serves 4.

title: granola cookies
directions: Blend the first 5 ingredients together.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Kids love these cookies!

title: enchiladas - family style
directions: Brown hamburger; mix with beans.
Add sauces and enough water to make it soupy.
Spoon bean mixture in baking dish.
Place tortillas over bean mixture.
Layer meat, cheese and tortillas, ending with beans and cheese.
Bake in moderate oven until cheese is melted.
Serve with lettuce and sour cream.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together in large bowl potatoes, undiluted chicken soup, butter, salt, onions, shredded cheese and sour cream.
Mix together corn flakes and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Place first mixture in greased 11 x 13-inch pan, cover top with corn flake mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook slowly for two hours.
Keep stirred well.
Add water or tomato sauce to keep from burning.

title: porkypine balls
directions: Add water, enough to cover meat balls.
Pour over meat balls and bake in 375° oven for 1 hour or until done.
Serves 6.

title: potato salad
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Chill and serve on lettuce cup or a nest of alfalfa sprouts.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Stir in flour.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool slightly.
Remove from cookie sheet.

title: buster bar dessert
directions: Mix Oreos and 1/2 cup butter.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread ice cream over Oreos.
Boil chocolate chips, Hershey's syrup, milk and butter for 8 minutes.
Stir constantly; remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Cool and spread over ice cream.
Freeze 24 hours.

title: 7 layer casserole
directions: In a large casserole bowl place ingredients in this order: rice, corn with juice, onion, green pepper, salt, pepper, 1 can tomato sauce, 1 can water, ground beef, 1 can tomato sauce and bacon slices.
Cover with foil or lid and bake for 1 1/2 hours in 400° oven.
Remove foil about 15 minutes before end of baking time. Serve with flour tortillas.

title: bologna boat
directions: Fry bologna until it forms into a cup.
Prepare potatoes according to directions on box.
Fill bologna cups with potatoes. Cover with cheese.
Broil at 350° until cheese melts.
Serve hot.

title: plain potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and onion together; drain and mash.
Blend with mayonnaise.
Remove yolks from eggs; mash.
Blend with 3 tablespoons mayonnaise and mustard.
Chop egg whites.
Combine with potatoes and yolk mixture.

title: carrot loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in well buttered loaf pan.

title: squash relish
directions: Soak squash overnight in refrigerator covered in water with 1/2 cup salt. Drain salt water off squash and wash well and drain again.

title: mixed vegetable salad
directions: Heat 1-inch salted water to boiling.
Add cauliflower and broccoli.
Cover and reduce heat.
Cook 5 minutes.
