Rinse under cold water; drain.
Rinse peas under cold water to thaw; drain. Mix mayonnaise, yogurt, lemon juice, salt and pepper in 2 1/2-quart bowl.
Add cauliflower, broccoli, peas and carrots. Toss.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Stir in tomatoes.

title: mama's macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter. Add flour and mix well, forming a roux.
Add salt, pepper, milk and then cheese. Stir until thick and pour over 1 cup cooked macaroni.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in butter. Drain excess grease. Cook macaroni by directions; drain. In deep casserole, build up in layers the meat and onion mixture, macaroni and top with cheese. Pour 1/2 can of tomato soup and 1/4 cup of water (mixed) over it. Bake at 275° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Chill shrimp and, if large, cut into halves or quarters.
Add other ingredients and toss together. Chill and serve on lettuce. Serves 4 to 6 servings.

title: easy brownies
directions: Cream margarine; add sugar gradually.
Blend until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing after each addition.
Stir in chocolate syrup, flour and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and lightly floured 11 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until they test done with toothpick.
Do not overbake.
When cool, cut into about 35 (2-inch) squares.

title: date nut pudding
directions: Mix sugar, flour, baking powder, salt, egg, dates, milk and nuts.
Put into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar, water and butter; pour over batter.
Bake at 350° until golden crust, 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: ginger creams
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg, molasses and water; mix. Add remaining ingredients; mix until blended.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Heat oven to 400°.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls, about 2 inches apart, onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until almost no indentation remains when touched, about 8 minutes.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Cool. Frost with Vanilla Butter Frosting.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: deep dish brownies
directions: Blend butter, sugar and vanilla in bowl.
Add eggs and beat well with spoon.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt in separate bowl.
Gradually add to egg mixture until well blended. Spread in greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from edge of pan.

title: pizza pie
directions: Combine eggs and next 6 ingredients, mixing well.
Set aside.

title: lemonade pies
directions: Mix lemonade, Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip.
Fold into pie shells and refrigerate before serving.
Keep refrigerated.
Makes 2 pies.

title: freezer corn
directions: Cut corn off cobs in large pan.
Mix in remaining ingredients and place in oven at 325°.
Bake 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Remove pan from oven and place in sink that has been filled with ice water.
Package and freeze when corn has cooled.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add oil, sugar, zucchini, vanilla and honey; mix well.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add gradually to zucchini mixture.
Fold in nuts.

title: bishop cake
directions: Mix and bake cake mix as usual.
Prepare pudding as directed. Add cream cheese that has been at room temperature to the pudding.
When cake is cool, spread this mixture on top of cake, then spread 1 cup coconut over top of pudding mixture, then 1 large can of crushed pineapple (drain well) over coconut.
Then add Cool Whip on top; add nuts on top of that (you can use 3 packages of Dream Whip prepared as on box if you don't have Cool Whip).
Keep refrigerated.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Two teaspoons of mixture to 1 cup of boiling water is usual serving.

title: ranch stew
directions: Brown ground meat; drain fat.
Add soup, Ro-Tel and beans; let simmer until ready to serve.
Sometimes, I add corn.

title: chocolate truffle
directions: Bake cake according to box directions. Cool and cut up into small squares. Make pudding according to directions on the box. In truffle bowl, layer the above starting with the cake, pudding and Cool Whip. Sprinkle with the chocolate chips. Repeat until using all the ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: herbed mushroom bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and line a loaf pan with waxed paper.
Tear bread into small pieces (should be about 9 cups) onto a baking sheet.
Bake 15 minutes, until dry.
Set aside.
Reduce oven heat to 250°.
Saute onion in butter in a large frying pan until limp.
Add mushrooms and cook until the liquid has almost evaporated.
Add wine and spices and cook 3 minutes.
Transfer mixture to a large bowl.
Add celery, bread, eggs, stock and salt and pepper to taste.
Let sit 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Pack into the prepared loaf pan.
Top with waxed paper and press firmly.
Place the loaf pan in a roasting pan with about 2 inches hot water and bake 1 hour.
Remove waxed paper from top.
Turn out onto a serving platter and remove remaining waxed paper.
Serve with gravy, if desired.
This is a great substitute for traditional dressing served with poultry.
Serves 8.

title: sally's green noodle lamb casserole
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add garlic and onion.
Saute onion until transparent.
Add lamb and brown; drain off fat.
To lamb add water, soup, tomato sauce, salt, oregano and pepper.
Simmer mixture gently.
When ready to assemble, layer lamb, noodles and cheese and repeat.
Bake 15 minutes, covered, at 350° in 8 x 12-inch pan (sprayed with Pam) for 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: mustard roast
directions: Prick with large fork all over both sides of meat.
Pour small amount of oil on meat and rub in.
Slit fat to keep from curling. Cover each side with garlic salt, pepper, chili powder and mustard.
Lay on platter.
Marinate 2 to 4 hours.

title: vegetables with pasta
directions: Cook fettuccine according to package directions.
Rinse with hot water; drain.
Meanwhile, in a 10-inch skillet melt butter until sizzling; add broccoli, mushrooms, carrots, onion and garlic.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are crisply tender (4 to 5 minutes).
Stir in basil, salt and pepper.
Add fettuccine and cheese.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until cheese is melted (3 to 5 minutes). Makes 6 servings.
One serving has 240 calories, 11 g Fat, 20 mg cholesterol and 330 mg sodium.

title: reese's peanut butter cups
directions: Melt and mix together all above ingredients in a double boiler.
Put about 1 teaspoon of mixture in a cupcake paper; roll around sides.
Refrigerate until chocolate is completely chilled. When thoroughly chilled, put 1 teaspoon peanut butter in center of cup, then cover with chocolate mixture.

title: tomato relish
directions: Combine tomatoes, onions and salt in bowl.
Let stand overnight and then drain.
In a large pot, add vinegar, ground cloves, black pepper, dry mustard and allspice.
Simmer, stirring often, for 3 hours.
Add sugar and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes more.
Put in sterile jars.
Delicious with pork, chicken or ham.

title: amanda's zesty italian
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Place this in 9 x 13-inch or 7 x 11-inch pan.
Grate the cheese and add the sour cream.
Spread over meat mixture.
Top with crescent rolls, unrolled.
If desired, crumble 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese and 2 tablespoons melted margarine evenly over dough.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 25 minutes.

title: delicate, fluffy buttermilk pancakes
directions: Beat egg yolks; beat in buttermilk and soda.
Sift together and beat in flour, sugar and salt.
Beat in butter and gently fold in egg whites.
Bake on hot griddle.

title: banana cake
directions: Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until top springs back when touched.
Ice as you like.

title: deep-dish blackberry cobbler
directions: Combine berries, sugar, flour, lemon juice and salt; stir well.
Prepare pastry and divide dough in half.
Roll half of dough to 1/8-inch thickness to fit sides and bottom of a lightly greased 2-quart baking dish.
Spoon half of berry mixture into pastry-lined dish; dot with half of butter.

title: baked macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Shred sharp Cheddar cheese.
In a buttered dish place 1/2 of the macaroni and half of the cheese. Sprinkle salt and pepper over it.
Place remaining macaroni and cheese.
Put oleo in small pieces over the casserole and cook at 375° until cheese is melted all the way through.

title: homemade scrapple(an old pennsylvania dutch recipe)
directions: Cook meat, covered in boiling salted water at simmering until meat falls from bones.
Remove meat from broth.
Cut or grind into small pieces.
Strain broth into top of a double boiler.
Add cornmeal and cook over direct heat for 5 minutes, stirring constantly to prevent lumping.
(Mixture needs to be very thick.) Add meat and chopped onion; season to taste.
Cook over boiling water for 1 hour.
Pack into loaf pans and store in the refrigerator.

title: crock-pot potatoes
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan and add sour cream and soup. Combine with cooked potatoes in crock-pot on low.
Heat for one hour.
Delicious!

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Then add 2 diced tomatoes. Stir lightly.
Put in bowl and garnish with fresh parsley.

title: mushroom gravy
directions: Saut minced onion and garlic in hot olive oil in a medium saucepan over medium heat until tender. Add sliced mushrooms and saut 5 minutes. Stir in beef broth and soy sauce. Stir together cornstarch and 3/4 cup water. Gradually stir into broth mixture. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Boil for 1 minute. Stir in salt and pepper.

title: dill pickles
directions: You will also need bottling jars, lids and rings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together, shortening and sugar. Add eggs and beat well. Sift together dry ingredients. Add to creamed mixture alternately with bananas, blending well after each addition. Stir in nuts.

title: jennie's stuffed artichokes
directions: Cut stems from artichokes, creating a flat base; snip off pointed leaves top.
Cut away bottom row of leaves; on a flat board, turn choke upside down and pound until leaves separate. Wash chokes thoroughly.
Combine breadcrumbs and cheese and spoon into and between artichoke leaves; drizzle olive oil onto stuffed chokes and place in large covered pot.
Add water and steam over low flame for 40 minutes.
Melt butter and dip leaves in butter when serving.
Serve with Chianti or Merlot.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Mix rolled oats, brown sugar, salt and shortening.
Pour boiling water and scalded milk over this.
Let cool.

title: herb butter
directions: Beat all together at high speed in small mixer bowl until fluffy.
Keep in tightly covered container in refrigerator.
Melt some to brush on hot corn-on-the-cob.
Excellent with hot vegetables or broiled fish, steak or poultry.

title: applesauce cake roll
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add raisins and set aside.
Beat eggs until thick.
Add sugar gradually and beat until thick and ivory colored.
Fold in applesauce.
Gently fold in flour and raisins. Pour into prepared jelly roll pan.*
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Turn out on towel sprinkled with confectioners sugar. Trim wax paper from cake and roll up in towel (like jelly roll). Cool 10 minutes.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix the pie filling and pineapple together. Stir in the milk. Mix in the vanilla. Fold in the Cool Whip. Chill and serve.

title: caramelized apple quarters
directions: Caramelize the sugar to amber color, put in apples, and stir until coated.
Reduce heat and stir constantly.
Add butter and stir for 1 to 2 minutes longer.
Butter a glass pie dish and put the caramelized apples in.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: salt substitute
directions: Mix them all thoroughly and place the mixture in a shaker. Store the shaker in a cool, dark place to preserve the flavor until the mixture can be used up.

title: hidden treasure strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in fruits and nuts. Pour half of gelatin mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2 in. dish.
Chill until firm.
Store remaining gelatin mixture at room temperature. Prepare cheesecake filling according to package directions. (Reserve graham cracker crumbs for other uses.)
Spoon cheesecake filling over congealed fruit mixture.
Spoon remaining gelatin mixture over filling and chill until firm.

title: pork chops with chicken noodle gravy
directions: Wash pork chops and dry with paper towel.
Baste both sides with mustard.
Place in skillet with bottom covered with vegetable oil.
Cook on medium temperature until brown.
Drain oil.
Add chicken noodle soup and water.
Stir and cover.
Reduce to low and simmer 30 minutes.
Serve over mashed potatoes or rice.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Place ground vegetables in crock-pot; add salt.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Put into colander and rinse well with cold water to remove salt.
Heat remaining ingredients; bring to a boil and boil 30 minutes.
Put into jars and seal.
It is recommended that jars then be processed in water bath for 10 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and vinegar in water.
Cook until mixture spins a thread.
Add peanuts and cook until all peanuts have popped and mixture turns a gold color.
Add salt and butter.
Add soda; stir well.
Pour on a buttered cookie sheet.
Cool and break into pieces.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and water.
Let stand until jelled slightly (thick, but not solid).

In the meantime, drain pineapple very well and soak marshmallows in this until Jell-O is ready. When Jell-O is ready to be beaten, beat until it is foamy. Whip the cream very well. Fold into the Jell-O the pineapple, whipped cream, marshmallows and juice.
Put into an 8 x 8-inch dish or pan and let stand overnight in refrigerator. Cut, serve and enjoy.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preparation Time:
1 1/2 hours.
Peel and slice apples thinly. Put in shallow 1-quart casserole and sprinkle with water.
Sift dry ingredients and cut in butter until well combined.
Sprinkle mixture thickly and evenly over apples.
Do not mix the two.
Cover casserole and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Uncover and bake another 1/2 hour.
Crust will be crisp on top.
Number of servings:
6 to 8.

title: egg in a hole
directions: Put a little butter in pan.
Tear small hole in bread.
Put bread on butter in the pan.
Break egg into hole.
Chop egg yolk slightly, let cook for 5 minutes, then flip egg and bread over once.
Let cook 5 minutes more.
Butter may be added then eat.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie pan with pastry.
Put in a large bowl sugar, flour and corn meal.
Toss lightly with a fork.
Add eggs (unbeaten), butter (melted), milk and lemon rind and juice.
Beat with mixer until smooth and blended well.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes or until top is golden brown. Cut warm.

title: salsa
directions: Combine olives, chiles, green onion, tomato and spices in bowl; mix well.
Stir in vinegar and olive oil.
Chill until serving time.
Serve with corn chips.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: mexicale pork chop casserole(4 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown chops in hot mixture.
Saute green peppers and onion in skillet until tender.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bring to boil.
Spoon into 3-quart casserole.
Arrange pork chops on top.
Bake, covered, for 35 minutes; uncovered 15 minutes longer.

title: dill pickle
directions: Combine sugar, salt, vinegar, water and spices.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Pack cukes into hot jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace. Put a head of dill weed in each jar on top of cucumbers.
Heat; bring to boiling.
Pour over cukes.
Seal jars.
Process in boiling water for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from water; place on towels. Cover with towels until cool.
Store in a cool, dark place.

title: oven fried chicken legs
directions: *I use powdered milk, mixed.

title: beef porcupines(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Combine V-8 juice, sugar and Worcestershire sauce in a 10-inch skillet.
Stir.
Combine the other ingredients in a mixing bowl. Mix well.
Shape into balls about the size of walnuts and place in V-8 mixture.
Cook, covered, on low heat for about 40 minutes or until done.

title: turkey soup with barley
directions: Cut turkey carcass to fit 5-quart casserole.
Place in casserole with hot water; cover.
Microwave at High for 1 hour. Remove carcass.
Remove meat from bones.
Discard bones and skin. Add meat, barley, onion, celery, carrots, salt and pepper to water.
Re-cover.
Microwave at High for 1 to 1 1/4 hours, or until barely is tender.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Cook cabbage in salted water a few minutes to soften.
Drain. Mix 2 tablespoons soup with remaining ingredients.
Divide meat mixture among cabbage leaves; fold in sides and roll up, securing with toothpicks if needed.
Place seam side down in pan or casserole.
Place remaining soup on top of each roll.
Bake in oven 2 hours at 325° to 350°.
Spoon sauce over rolls several times.
(I use a pan and cover with aluminum foil.)

title: crab meat hors d'oeuvres
directions: Blend first six ingredients. Spread mixture on split muffins. Sprinkle with paprika. Put in freezer for approximately one hour. Cut each into wedges. Can be refrozen and kept in plastic bags until ready to be baked and served. Cook at 350° until hot and bubbly.
Makes approximately 72.

title: goulash
directions: Brown beef, onion and rest of ingredients except cheese. Simmer for 1 hour.
Top with cheese and heat until cheese melts.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour three 8-inch pans.

title: spinach salad
directions: Ingredients may be prepped ahead and ready to toss (except for fresh mushrooms).
Toss everything together with 1/2 to 3/4 jar dressing.
Hormel real bacon pieces can be substituted for bacon.

title: mini cheese cakes
directions: Place one wafer in each cupcake paper.

title: rice salad
directions: Combine pineapple, lemon juice, sugar and salt.
Fold mixture into whipped cream and fold in rice and coconut.
Chill before serving.

title: tammy's cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add 1/2 flour; mix well.
Set aside.
Mix nuts, chocolate chips and raisins with the other half of the flour.
Add to egg mixture. Will be very stiff, use hands. Bake in greased and floured loaf or Bundt pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour. Cool in pan completely before removing.

title: barbecue
directions: Take good meaty parts of chicken (raw) and roll in Kraft hickory-smoke flavored barbecue sauce and lay in baking pan.
Put a piece of tinfoil over top (loosely).
I often fix this Sunday morning.
Put in 225°
oven at 9 o'clock.
When we come home from church it's done nicely.

title: orange pineapple dessert
directions: Mix dry jello with cottage cheese, then add drained pineapple and oranges.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in refrigerator until set.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dump pineapple in 13 x 9-inch pan. Dump cherry pie filling evenly on top.
Sprinkle almond extract over all.
Sprinkle yellow cake mix (directly from box) on top. Sprinkle nuts on cake mix.
Cut butter into pats and place on top. Bake 35 to 45 minutes until brown on top.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beat well after adding each egg.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk and bananas.
Stir in walnuts.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan at 350° for 65 minutes or until done.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water.
Allow to cool.
Cream butter and sugar (see Note) until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each.
Blend in vanilla and cooled chocolate.

title: low-fat yogurt fruit cream pie
directions: Mix desired flavors of fruit yogurt into whipped topping. Fill pie shell and chill for 1 hour.
Can double recipe.

title: chocolate pie(microwave)
directions: Scald milk in microwave.
Combine dry ingredients and stir into milk.
Beat the egg yolks and add gradually, stirring constantly.
Add salt and oleo.
Return to microwave and heat on High 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir and return again and heat 3 to 4 more minutes or until thick.
Add vanilla.
Cool and pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue made of the 3 egg whites.
Bake until meringue is brown.

title: egg souffle
directions: Bring water to barely boiling.
Break egg into a saucer; slide from saucer into the water.
Cook just until whites are done. Heat Canadian bacon.
Toast English muffin.

title: cranberry catsup
directions: Tie spices in a bag. Boil cranberries and liquid until cranberries are tender.
Remove spices and run cranberries through a sieve.
Add sugar.
Boil 10 minutes and seal in sterile jars. Makes 1 quart.

title: cheese danish
directions: In a 9 x
13-inch pan, unroll crescent rolls and put in bottom of pan.
Mix
cream
cheese
(softened),
sugar and egg yolk. Spread over
crescent
rolls.
Add	other
can crescent rolls and spread over
cream	cheese mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Mix brown sugar, margarine, Karo and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove pan from heat.
Stir in vanilla and soda.
Put popcorn in buttered roasting pan.
Pour hot syrup over corn; mix well.
Bake at 250° for one hour, stirring occasionally.

title: ham-chutney rolls
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Spread on the 6 slices of ham.
Dot each with 1 1/2 teaspoon sweet chutney.
Roll up.
Cut into 1-inch slices.
Cover and chill.
Yields 30 rolls.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Add fruit to gelatin and process until fairly smooth. Add sugar substitute and extracts.
Chill until set.

title: green rice
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Saute onions, add soups and bring to a boil.
Drain broccoli and add to soup mixture.
Add Cheez Whiz and cook slowly until melted.
Add cooked rice and mix well. If mixture seems too thick, add a little milk to thin.
Place in greased casserole dish and sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
(May be divided into 2 casseroles and one frozen.)

title: baked zucchini casserole
directions: Wash and cut squash in 1/4-inch thick pieces.
Line bottom of dish with same and add part of bread cubes, tomatoes, pepper, onion, a layer of cheese and salt and pepper to taste.
Repeat procedure with cheese on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: worlds best cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream together butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Add egg, mixing well, then salad oil, mixing well.
Add oats, corn flakes, coconut and nuts, stirring well.
Add flour, soda and nuts.
Mix well and form into balls the size of small walnuts.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in water.
Bake 12 minutes.
Allow to cool on cookie sheet a few minutes before removing.
(If substituting walnuts for the coconut, it takes longer to bake than 12 minutes.)
Makes 8 dozen cookies.

title: nut goodie bars
directions: Melt chips and chocolate.
Add peanut butter.
Mix.
Spread 1/2 of mixture in a 12 x 16-inch greased pan.
Put in freezer to set.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle in 1/4 of the stuffing mix.
Layer chicken and mushrooms.
Combine sour cream, chicken soup and 1 cup of broth; mix well and pour over chicken and mushrooms.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing mix over chicken.
Pour on enough of remaining broth to moisten stuffing mix.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and oil.
Stir in grated zucchini.
Add flour which has been added salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add vanilla.
Add remaining 1/2 cup flour to raisin and nuts.
Then add remaining ingredients to mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: classic coleslaw
directions: Combine cabbage, carrots, salt, pepper and liquid red-pepper seasoning in large bowl.
Add basic dressing made of mayonnaise, sour cream and Dijon mustard.
Stir until cabbage is evenly coated with dressing.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: cinnamon candy
directions: In heavy 4-quart pot with lid, add sugar, water, syrup and salt.
Cook and stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Be careful it doesn't boil over.
After it comes to a boil, cover with lid. Cook for 1 minute, covered, then remove lid.
Cook over medium heat until candy is 300° or the hard crack stage on candy thermometer.
You don't have to stir.
Candy will change color. When dipped in cold water, will become hard.
Remove from heat and stir in margarine, food coloring and cinnamon oil.
Be careful with the cinnamon oil, it will burn your eyes and nose.
Grease 3 (9 x 13-inch) pans.
Pour into pans.
Let cool; break it up with a spoon.

title: devil's food mincemeat bars
directions: Cook mincemeat slowly in 1/2 cup water for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool.
Add nuts and dry cake mix.
Beat well.
Gradually add remaining 1/2 cup of water, stirring until blended.
Pour into greased 14 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.
When cool, cut into bars.
(Some people cut into bars and cover with powdered sugar.)

title: right now nachos
directions: Arrange tortilla chips in a 9-inch microwave-safe pie plate. Drizzle a few drops of taco sauce over each chip.
Sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese over chips.
Cook, uncovered, on 100% power for 30 to 45 seconds or until cheese is melted.
Let cooked nachos stand for 1 minute before eating.
Makes 18.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix margarine, peanut butter, white sugar, brown sugar, egg, flour, soda, salt and baking powder in that order.
Roll in balls; press down with a fork.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: cherry nut coffee cake
directions: Mix walnuts, cinnamon and 4 tablespoons sugar; set aside. Drain cherries.
Cut cherries in halves and set aside.
Sift flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Cream butter with 1 cup sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs; mix well.
Add flour mixture and sour cream.

title: snack pretzels
directions: Add onion soup mix to melted butter and stir.
Pour mixture over pretzels and stir and mix until pretzels are coated.
Place in two 8 1/2 x 13-inch cake pans (these fit side by side in my oven) with oven rack in middle of oven.
Bake for 1 hour at 225°; stir every 15 minutes.

title: fresh vegetable pizza
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 4 long rectangles. Place rectangles crosswise into ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Press over bottom and up sides.
Seal perforations.
Bake 14 to 19 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.
Blend sour cream, horseradish, salt and pepper.
Spread over top.
Top with vegetables.
Cut into small pieces.
Store in refrigerator. Makes 60 appetizers.

title: 1000 island dressing
directions: Mix ingredients together and refrigerate.
Serve over lettuce or tossed salad.

title: molly's irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Soak raisins in hot water for 10 minutes.
Combine dry ingredients.
Melt butter and combine with dry ingredients.
Drain raisins and combine with dry ingredients. Combine eggs and buttermilk; beat thoroughly.
Pour egg mixture into dry ingredients.
Stir or knead until thoroughly mixed.
Bake in two regular size loaf pans for 1 hour (375°).

title: old fashioned gingerbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 1 hour.

title: new year's pork-n-kraut
directions: Place pork roast, fat side up, and rub with spices.
Place sauerkraut around roast and cover halfway with water.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for about 4 hours.
After about 3 1/2 hours, uncover and let cook dry for the last half hour.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Beat 5 egg whites stiffly. Cream margarine with shortening. Add sugar, beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat well.
Sift flour and soda together.
Add to mixture with buttermilk, coconut, pecans and egg whites.
Flour and grease 3 cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients through the hard-boiled eggs.
Mix melted butter and crushed Ritz crackers.
Place first mixture in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Add cracker topping and sliced almonds. Cook at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: 3-layer candy
directions: Combine sugar and syrup.
Cook over medium heat until dissolved, stirring constantly. Add peanut butter and cereal. Stir and press into a 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Let cool.
Melt chocolate morsels and spread over mixture.
Let cool. Melt butterscotch morsels.
Spread over chocolate layer.
Let cool.
Cut into pieces and serve.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
In blender, grate cheese and bread. Add spices.
Dip chicken
in melted margarine, then in seasoning; coat.
Place
chicken
in
baking
dish.	Drizzle remaining margarine over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Refrigerate.
Serve with dark brown bread.

title: bar-b-cups
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add barbecue sauce to taste.
Use canned biscuits to make shells in a muffin tin.
Fill with ground beef mixture and top with grated cheese.
Bake in 400° oven until done.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all, except peanut butter.
Let boil for 10 minutes.
Add the peanut butter.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: bear biscuits
directions: Melt margarine, chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Pour over Crispix in a very large bowl and mix well.
Shake powdered sugar in a clean brown grocery bag; add cereal mixture and shake well until individual pieces are coated.
Store in airtight container.

title: judy's ginger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and molasses.
Add all dry ingredients sifted together.
Form in little balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: celery pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in ice water for 2 hours.
Cut in strips and pack in jars.
Heat vinegar, sugar, salt and celery seed to boiling.
Pour over cucumbers. Check tops of jars so no seeds will be under lids.
Seal.

title: peanut butter loaf
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Mix and sift the first 4 ingredients. Cream shortening and peanut butter.
Add sugar gradually while creaming.
Continue to cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Stir in dry ingredients alternately with mashed bananas.
Mix well, but do not beat.
Spoon batter into well-greased loaf pan (8 x 4 x 3-inch).
Bake 1 hour.

title: old reliable vegetable soup
directions: In a large soup kettle, bring water and soup bones to a boil. Skim foam from surface and let boil gently while you prepare the vegetables.
As they are peeled and chopped, add carrots, onions and potatoes.
Add tomatoes and return kettle to a boil.
Stir in lima beans, corn and okra and let cook a few minutes.
Stir in cabbage, then add salt and pepper to taste.
Let simmer for at least 45 minutes.
Makes about 12 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening until light and fluffy. Stir in eggs, pumpkin and water.
Sift together all dry ingredients and add gradually to pumpkin mixture.
Add nuts and dates and blend well.
Turn batter into 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in oblong baking pan and sprinkle with 12 ounce package of butterscotch bits.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: venison roast
directions: Wrap roast with bacon and secure with toothpicks. Put in crock-pot and add all other ingredients. Cook slow in crock-pot until tender.

title: hamburger pie
directions: In large skillet, cook meat and onion until meat is lightly browned and onion is tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add green beans and soup.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mash potatoes while hot.
Add milk and egg.
Season with salt and pepper.
Spoon in mounds over casserole.
Sprinkle potatoes with cheese.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and soda.
Blend in lard.
Add hot water.
Mix well.
Roll out.
Place in freezer for easier handling.

title: elsie dodge's watermelon pickles
directions: Cut rind in 2-inch strips.
Soak in brine 24 hours, using 1/3 cup salt to one quart water.
Rinse, drain and cook in boiling water until tender.
Tie spices in bag and boil 20 minutes with vinegar and sugar.
Add melon rind and cook slowly 1/2 hour. Place in jars. Seal.

title: puppy chow(snack mix)
directions: Melt peanut butter, chocolate chips and butter in saucepan and pour over cereal.
Let cool slightly.
Put in large bag with 3 cups 10x sugar and shake.

title: old fashioned bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight and drain.
Cover with fresh water, add ham and bring to a boil.
Add the remaining ingredients and simmer until potatoes are tender.

title: zucchini and swiss cheese bake
directions: Butter a casserole dish and spread zucchini slices in bottom. Scatter tomatoes on top.
Dot with margarine.
Add salt and pepper.
Top with Swiss cheese slices.
Sprinkle with sage.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: creole okra
directions: Put okra in pan of cold water; bring to a boil.
Drain.
Do this 3 times. The last time, add a little salt.
It's ready to eat.

title: paella(party fare)
directions: Note:
A traditional Paella pan or a large open pan with a fairly thick bottom should be used as this is a slow cooked one pan preparation.

title: potato salad
directions: Dice egg whites and add with the onions to diced potatoes.

title: doves braised in vegetables
directions: Saute the doves in butter until lightly browned in the casserole dish.
Set birds aside.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Don't peel squash until skin is tough.
Grind squash, onions, peppers and salt.
Let stand overnight.

title: okra corn bread
directions: Mix and put in greased iron pan.
Put in cold oven.
Bake at 350° until set and brown.

title: schaum torte
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar gradually, beating until mixture will hold its own weight.
Add vanilla and vinegar. Pour into a spring cake form.
Bake in slow oven (300°) for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool.

title: caramel chocolate fingers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk in heavy saucepan.
Heat and stir until blended; keep warm.
Combine dry cake mix, melted butter and 1/3 cup evaporated milk in bowl.
Mix well.
Spread half of mixture in bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge cake
directions: In saucepan, combine butter, cocoa, water, buttermilk and eggs.
Stir constantly over low heat until bubbles.
In large bowl, mix sugar, soda and flour together.
Stir hot mixture into dry mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350° or until firm to touch. Cool some.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef or sausage.
Drain grease.
Add sauce, wine, garlic powder and basil.
Stir and microwave on High for 7 to 8 minutes.
In a mixing bowl, combine the Ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese, parsley, egg and pepper.
Spoon the meat sauce to cover the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Arrange 4 noodles on the sauce. Spread half the cheese mixture and then half the Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat procedure with sauce as the final layer.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 6 minutes, then on 70% (Medium High) for 20 minutes.
Let casserole rest for 12 to 15 minutes before serving.
Standing time is crucial to the success of this recipe.
Do not serve before letting stand!

title: meatless spaghetti
directions: In large saucepan, or a Dutch oven, saute garlic, celery and onion in oil until tender.
Add zucchini, green pepper and olives; saute for 2 to 3 minutes.
Dissolve bouillon in water; add to vegetables.
Add the next 10 ingredients and bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Serve over spaghetti.
Yields 14 servings.

title: peach-coconut pecan crisp
directions: Layer ingredients in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Peaches, cake mix (be sure to sprinkle cake mix dry), dribble butter over dry cake mix, then flaked coconut and pecans last.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Serve with ice cream.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender. Add remaining ingredients. Cook until vegetables are tender.

title: frosting
directions: In top of double boiler, cook flour and milk until thick. Stir in chocolate until melted.
Cool.
Cream the sugar and oleo until fluffy.
Add flour mixture and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix in one bowl the first 6 ingredients.
Mix in another bowl the next 5 ingredients.
Mix dry ingredients into other mixture. Spread in greased and floured (large) cookie sheet or two small cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Bake white cake mix in 9 x 13 pan.
After cake is cooled, spread 1/2 can of crushed pineapple with the juice on top.
Mix together cream cheese, milk and vanilla pudding.
Spread over the pineapple and top with a layer of Cool Whip.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Marinate 6 chicken breasts for 4 to 6 hours, then barbecue.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Blend avocados and cream cheese.
Add chopped onion and 1/2 can tomatoes and chilies.
Whip in blender.
Add lemon juice; whip until creamy.
Chill.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Stir sugar, corn syrup and water over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Without stirring, drop small amount in cold water until it forms a hard ball.
Beat egg whites until peaks form, pouring hot syrup in a thin stream into egg whites; add vanilla. Beat until mixture holds its shape and becomes slightly dull; fold in nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: ham and cheese hot dog bun sandwiches
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and spread on hot dog buns, as much as desired on each bun.
Place pieces of ham in bun, as much as desired.
Place 1/4 to 1/2 slice of each Swiss and American cheese in each bun.
Depending on how many sandwiches you need will determine how much you use of each item.
Wrap each filled bun with foil and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: plain italian cookies
directions: In a bowl, mix all ingredients.
With electric mixer, add 2 cups flour, a little at a time.
Fold in an additional 2 cups or more flour until stickiness disappears.
Spoon onto ungreased cookie sheet and round with fingers.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until bottoms are golden brown.
Makes 5 dozen or more. Cool.
Dip top of cookie into thin, watery frosting of confectioners sugar, lemon extract and milk or water.

title: butterfingers
directions: Mix ingredients together thoroughly.
Drop by tablespoon onto floured board.
Roll with hand.
Cut into finger lengths and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 300° for 20 minutes or until brown. Remove from pan with a spatula and roll in sifted confectioners sugar.
Be careful when you take the cookies from the oven as they will break easily.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onions, salt and pepper in a small amount of water. Drain. Add sugar and cream cheese. Beat with electric mixer until well blended and creamy.
Add egg. Put into a buttered casserole dish. Top with crushed crackers that have been mixed with the melted butter. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: low-fat chocolate pound cake
directions: Coat the bottom of an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan with cooking spray; dust with flour and set aside.
Combine cake flour and the next 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Add oil, milk and vanilla; beat at medium speed until batter is smooth (batter will be thick).
Add one third of egg whites; stir mixture gently. Fold in the remaining egg whites.
Pour batter into prepared pan. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes, or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool pan 10 minutes; remove from pan. Cool on wire rack.
Yields 16 servings.

title: chicken berry salad
directions: Prepare dressing as directed on package using vinegar and oil and substituting orange juice for water.
Toss remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pizza salad
directions: In large bowl, combine cooked pasta, tomatoes, Cheddar cheese, onion and pepperoni.
In small bowl, combine oil, Parmesan cheese, vinegar and seasonings; pour over pasta mixture.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours.
Yields 16 servings.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix first five ingredients; pour into a 9 x 13 inch pan. Sprinkle top with brown sugar and pecans. Bake at 350° until done.

title: dirt cake
directions: Freeze cookies and crush in blender as fine as possible.
Mix pudding and milk in blender or with beater.
In large bowl, cream margarine, confectioners sugar and cream cheese with electric mixer.
Add pudding and mix thoroughly.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer crushed cookies, filling cookies in dish or flower pot (10 to 12-inch).
End with thick layer of cookie crumbs on top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 loaf pans (5 x 9-inch).
Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat pumpkin, oil, eggs, water and sugar in large bowl. Sift dry ingredients and add to pumpkin mixture.
Pour into loaf pans and bake at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt and soda together.
Cut in shortening. Add yeast and buttermilk.
Knead well.
(It may be necessary to knead in more flour.)
Cut out biscuits and bake at 450°.
Dough may be covered and refrigerated for a week.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli florets into bite-sized pieces. Add all cheese, bacon and onion.
Mix dressing.

title: crabmeat stuffed tomatoes
directions: In a bowl put crab meat, rice, peppers, onions and parsley. Add mayonnaise and sour cream (combined).
Add lemon, salt and cayenne.
Mix well.
Refrigerate.
Slice top off each tomato and set sliced end down (so it will stand freely).
Cut each tomato into sections, being careful not to slice entirely through and fill with crabmeat salad.
Refrigerate one hour and serve on bed of lettuce.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheet to 350°.
In large bowl, stir first 5 ingredients until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into crust.
Bake on cookie sheet for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edges comes out clean.
Serves 8.

title: grandma greene's peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, canned milk and oleo in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently.
Boil until soft ball test.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter, Marshmallow Creme and walnuts.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.

title: fish casserole
directions: Spread fillets with mayo.
Mix cheese and crumbs.
Roll fish in mixture.
Place in buttered pan.
Top with rest of crumbs. Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lemon poppy seed cake
directions: Combine cake mix and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Add vegetable oil and next 4 ingredients.
Beat at medium speed with an electric mixer 6 minutes.
Stir in poppy seed.
Pour batter in a 10-cup Bundt pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in the center of cake comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.

title: mustard dipping sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring until smooth.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Makes 1 cup.

title: italian sweet and sour dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a jar with tight fitting lid. Shake well.
Refrigerate.

title: apple carrot delight
directions: Place carrots and apples in saucepan; add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, over low heat for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until water boils down.

title: window cleaner
directions: Bless my little kitchen, Lord

title: peach upside-down cake
directions: In a small saucepan, combine brown sugar and 1/2 stick butter; melt, stirring to combine.
Spread on bottom of cake pan (9 x 3-inches deep).
Arrange peaches over brown sugar in concentric circles.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and cinnamon.
In a large bowl, beat remaining 1 1/2 sticks butter with granulated sugar until creamy.
Beat in egg yolks. Alternately beat in flour mixture with milk and vanilla until well blended.
In small bowl, beat egg whites to stiff peaks.
Fold egg whites into batter.
Spread over peach slices.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes at 350° or until a cake tester comes out clean.
Cool on rack 10 minutes.
Turn cake onto serving plate.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; place in 2-quart casserole dish.

title: beer-cheese fondue
directions: Melt butter in fondue pot.
Add cornstarch, paprika and mustard.
Add beer and stir until thickened, turning heat to medium.
Turn heat off and add cut up cheese.
Return to medium heat, stirring until cheese is melted.
Turn back to low and dip cubes of bread on forks.

title: mock pate
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and season with dill to taste.
Chill. Mold into ball or log and decorate with nuts.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream the soft butter and sugar.
Add salt and gradually add flour.
Pat down into 2 buttered 8 x 8-inch pans.
Prick surface with a fork.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle with granulated sugar.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Cut into squares, then cool completely before removing from pan.

title: you're lucky if there's any left
directions: Melt butter and mix with flour and pecans.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, 1 package Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Put on crust.
Mix pudding with the milk and put on top of cream cheese layer.
Spread the other package of Cool Whip next.
This is your top layer.
Sprinkle with a few of the nuts to decorate.

title: brownies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together.
Stir in butter.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Sift flour and salt together; stir into cocoa mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into a greased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake in a 375° oven for 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix the ingredients and pour into pie shells.
Keep pies refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: nathan's special pudding
directions: In a large bowl, place a layer of cookies dipped in milk; spread Cool Whip over cookies.
Continue to layer until bowl is filled.
Garnish with grated Hershey's Kisses.

title: frozen fruit dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients with a mixer.
Use cupcake pan, lined with cupcake liners.
Fill them and freeze in freezer or put in one pan and cut individual servings.
When frozen, if you are not going to use right away, wrap in foil for future enjoyment.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except soup and potato chips in a 2-quart ovenware casserole.
Spread undiluted soup over top.
Sprinkle potato chips over soup.
Cover casserole.
Set selector control to "bake".
Cook for 20 minutes or until salad is hot throughout and is set.
Total cooking time: 20 minutes.
Recipe yields: 6 to 8 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix until smooth. Add 4 cups Cool Whip and mix again until smooth. Pour into graham cracker crust. Chill until firm.

title: banana cake
directions: Make in 8 or 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Increase by half for a 9 x 13-inch pan.
This is a never fail cake.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat until fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Sift 2 cups flour, salt and baking powder.
Add sifted ingredients to creamed mixture and beat. Dredge berries in remaining 1 cup flour.
Gently fold into creamed mixture.
Pour mixture into tube pan which has been buttered and coated with sugar.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serves 15.

title: no-bake cheese cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, margarine, cinnamon, and sugar to make crust.
Press into 9-inch spring form pan.
Heat milk and add marshmallows (1/3 at a time until melted), stirring constantly. Mix cream cheese until soft and creamy.
Add marshmallow mixture to cream cheese.
Blend well.	Fold whipped cream into cheese mixture. Pour over graham cracker crust and chill.
Serves 6-8.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain grease and add taco seasoning per package directions.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix
all
ingredients together until well blended.
Roll into small balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Press down on pan with
a
fork.
Bake
in
preheated
oven 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown.
Also, depending on how crunchy you want the cookies to be.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form into balls.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
If frozen, add 15 minutes to baking time.

title: floyd's avocado soup
directions: Puree all.
Garnish with tomatoes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: christmas cake
directions: Sift flour, measured.
Add baking powder and salt and sift again.
Cream shortening and butter together.
Add sugar and cream until blended.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
If you use a mixer, beat with slow speed; mix in lemon and brandy flavoring, almond, coconut and lemon peel.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Turn batter into greased and floured 9-inch tube pan.
Bake in slow oven (300°) for 1 1/2 hours.
When cool, store in airtight container.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt chocolate and marshmallows in the milk in a double boiler.
Chill until cooled.
Fold in whipped cream and mix well. Pour into graham cracker crust and refrigerate overnight.

title: easy oven meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients; shape into 20 (1 1/2-inch) balls.
Cook in ungreased oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch) in a 400° oven until light brown, 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sunshine fizz
directions: Mix first three ingredients and process in electric blender until smooth.
Stir in club soda.
Pour into soda glasses or punch cups and add a scoop of orange sherbet to each serving.

title: homestyle ham 'n cheese chowder
directions: Melt butter in 3-quart saucepan until sizzling. Stir in onion. Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until tender (3 to 4 minutes). Stir in flour until well mixed. Stir in red pepper, chicken broth, potatoes, sage and pepper. Cover. Continue cooking until potatoes are tender (15 to 20 minutes). Add all remaining ingredients. Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until heated through (8 to 10 minutes).

title: pizza burgers
directions: Mix the preceding ingredients and spread on halves of hamburg rolls.
Broil.
Makes large bowl.
Refrigerate.
Can make up and serve whenever you like.

title: jiffy oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring margarine, sugar, milk and cocoa to a boil and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add quick cooking oats, 4 tablespoons crunchy peanut butter and vanilla.
Drop on waxed paper to form cookies.

title: cheese and sausage strata
directions: Brown sausage over moderately high heat, breaking it up with a fork, and transfer with a slotted spoon to paper towels to drain. Brush a 1-quart souffle dish with some of the fat remaining in the skillet; arrange 1/3 of the bread cubes in the bottom and sprinkle them with 1/3 of the cheese.
Arrange sausage over the mixture. Add half the remaining bread and sprinkle half the remaining cheese over it.
Top with remaining bread and press layers down slightly.

title: pedernales chili
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer 50 minutes.
Yield 8 cups. 646 calories per cup.
29 grams protein.
26 grams carbohydrates. 27 grams fat.
78 mg. cholesterol.	358 mg. sodium.

title: leprechaun cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to box directions.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan for only 15 minutes; let cool.

title: family oven chicken
directions: Melt butter.
Add lemon juice, salt, garlic and pepper.
Place chicken in butter mixture and turn to coat.
Remove and set aside. Reserve remaining butter mixture.
In large, shallow baking pan, place potatoes evenly over bottom.
Pour broth over potatoes. Place chicken, skin side up, in single layer on top of potatoes. Pour remaining butter mixture over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for about an hour.
Uncover. Place under broiler for 5 minutes or until chicken is brown and crisp.

title: no sugar pineapple cake
directions: Beat eggs and cream with oleo.
Add vanilla, raisins, pineapple and orange juice.
Sift dry ingredients and add to first mixture, mixing well but lightly.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325°. Cover when removed from oven to keep moist.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Cut red onion into rings.
Combine all ingredients in a bowl. Mix and marinate overnight.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Grease 9-inch pie plate.
Pour all ingredients in a blender and blend at low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased plate. Sprinkle 1 cup of coconut on top* or blend the cup of coconut with other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: chip beef cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together (save enough beef to roll ball in).
Make a ball; roll into chipped beef.
This is delicious after it sits a day or so.

title: scripture cake(a christmas recipe)
directions: Follow Solomon's advice for making good boys.
The original recipe gives no direction for mixing.
Here is the translation as follows:
Cream Judges with Jeremiah (1/2 cup butter with 2 cups sugar); add 1 Samuel (2 tablespoons honey).
Add 6 Jeremiah (6 egg yolks); beat well.

Then add the 1 Kings (1 1/2 cups of sifted flour) with Amos (2 teaspoons baking powder), 2 Chronicles (spice, 2 teaspoons cinnamon, 1/2 teaspoon ginger, 1 teaspoon nutmeg and 1/2 teaspoon cloves) and a pinch of Leviticus (salt) alternately with Judges (1 cup milk).
Stir in Nahum (2 cups chopped figs), Numbers (2 cups chopped almonds) and 1 Samuel (2 cups raisins). Fold in 6 Jeremiah (6 stiffly beaten egg whites).
Bake in a well-greased tube pan at 300° for 2 hours.
This cake is good with New Year's eggnog.

title: easy wild rice dressing
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Make rice according to instructions on package.
Combine ingredients in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pickled shrimp
directions: Pour boiling water over the shrimp, salt, celery tips and pickling spice.
Simmer until pink.
Drain and cool with cold water.
Peel and devein.
Alternate shrimp and onion in a shallow dish.
Place bay leaves on top.
Mix the remaining ingredients well and pour over shrimp.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours before serving.
Serves 10 people.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Using an 8 x 12-inch or oblong Pyrex 2-quart dish, smooth cherry pie filling.
Place pineapple over pie filling.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Smooth dry cake mix over pineapple.
Melt margarine and spoon over cake mix.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: easy herbed chicken
directions: In a large skillet, brown chicken in butter until no longer pink in center; salt and pepper to taste.
Add wine and vegetables; cover and simmer 7 to 10 minutes until vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring occasionally.
Arrange on serving platter.
Sprinkle with basil.
Makes 4 servings.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix well and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Mix everything, except ginger ale.
Just before serving, add chilled ginger ale.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream
first
ingredients.
Boil
raisins in water 1 minute and cool a little.	Mix flour, oatmeal and soda together and stir into creamed mixture.
Now add vanilla and raisins and beat well. Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: spam and cheeseburgers
directions: Melt the cheese with margarine.
Combine with Spam mixture. Then add chili sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Spread over hamburg rolls.
Brown in oven.
Covers 8 rolls.

title: quick mayonnaise rolls
directions: Mix all the ingredients together with a spoon.
Drop by spoonful into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for about 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hot and spicy spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; add celery, bell pepper and onions.
Saute until tender.
Stir in seasonings and crushed Ro-Tel tomatoes. Add mushrooms and drained peas.
In a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, layer: cooked spaghetti, meat and vegetable mixture and grated cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: quick cookies
directions: Beat egg.
Add Cool Whip and cake mix.
Drop by spoonfuls into powdered sugar.
Shape into balls and place on cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Don't overbake!
Cover tightly to keep soft.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: mammy's ginger cake
directions: Add flour to make stiff dough. Rub with yolks of eggs; roll thin. Cut with cake cutter and bake.

title: broiled crabmeat canapes
directions: Blend together softened margarine and cheese.
Stir in mayonnaise, salts and crabmeat.
Spread on muffin halves.
Cut each half into 4 pieces.
You can freeze canapes until time to serve.
Before serving, broil until brown and bubbly.
Serve hot.

title: stephen's po'boy filets
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bacon.
Divide into 6-8 equal portions.
Form into 1-inch thick patties.
Wrap each patty with a slice of bacon and secure with a toothpick.
Cook on grill until done.

title: jason's green bean-potato soup
directions: Combine all ingredients; cook until heated thoroughly.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender then grip it and rip it. Roll your eye lids back an sip slowly.
Contributed by a very single guy.
Ladies, he's all yours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together broccoli and rice.
Add the Cheez Whiz.
Mix all together and bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 325°.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Melt 1	stick butter and saute onion, pepper and celery until tender.
Mix
together
peas and mushroom soup. Add the pimentos and saute mixture. Stir with spoon until well mixed. Place	in buttered
casserole dish and top with bread crumbs. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: simple taco dip
directions: In a small bowl, blend together the cream cheese, sour cream, avocado dip, lemon juice and pepper sauce. Spread on a platter, top with olives, chilis, onions, lettuce, tomatoes and cheddar cheese. Serve with tortilla chips.
10-12 Servings.

title: roasted rosemary chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Rinse chicken, removing skin. Pat dry. Arrange evenly in a shallow baking dish. Place the olive oil in a skillet over low heat and saute onions for 5 minutes.
Add garlic and cook, stirring 5 minutes longer. Add the minced rosemary leaves. Stir thoroughly. Remove from heat. Drizzle the onion mixture over the chicken.
Top with the marinara sauce. Pour the water into the bottom of the pan and bake until chicken is cooked, about 60 minutes. Baste often. Serve chicken on platter and spoon the sauce over the top.
Garnish with whole rosemary sprigs.

title: luke's favorite peanut butter bars
directions: Combine flour, baking soda and salt. Set aside. In mixer, beat sugar, butter, peanut butter, egg and vanilla until creamy. Blend in flour mixture. Stir in 1 cup mini M&M's. Press into greased 9 x 13 pan and top with 1/2 cup of mini M&M's. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: potato salad(a great potato salad - a must try!)
directions: Cook potatoes.
In the meantime, in a bowl, add oil, cider vinegar, salt and pepper.
After potatoes are cooked, drain.
Put into large bowl and pour bowl of oil, cider vinegar, salt and pepper over hot potatoes.
Let cool.
Then add hard-boiled eggs, chopped, and the rest of ingredients.
Serve.

title: homemade noodles
directions: In a large bowl, combine all the ingredients except the butter. Mix until a stiff dough forms. On a lightly floured work surface, roll the dough out to form a 16 x 20-inch rectangle. Cut into 1/4 x 5-inch strips and allow to sit for 5 minutes.

title: refrigerator-sliced cucumber salad
directions: Boil salt, celery seed, vinegar and sugar.
Pour hot over cucumbers and let stand in refrigerator for approximately 12 hours.
Keep container covered.

title: mint meringue
directions: Preheat oven for 15 minutes to 375°.
Beat whites until fluffy.
Add cream of tartar and sugar slowly, then salt.
Beat until very stiff.
Add vanilla and food coloring.
Fold in mint chocolate chips.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Put in oven; turn oven off and leave cookies in oven 4 to 5 hours or overnight without opening the oven.

title: ham-chicken casserole
directions: Cook "el dente" very fine spaghetti broken in 1-inch pieces. Drain.
Saute in margarine, onions and mushrooms.
Add, but do not cook, ham and chicken.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Blend sour cream and cottage cheese.
Pour over meat mixture and into greased 3-quart casserole.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Cook oleo, syrup, salt and brown sugar 5 minutes.
Add vanilla and soda.
Pour over corn and nuts.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour. Stir every 15 or 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli and onion until tender (30 minutes).
Mix mushroom soup and garlic salt into broccoli.
Mix cracker crumbs and melted butter together.
In casserole dish, make layer of broccoli, layer of cheese and layer of crumbs.
Repeat until full. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix together cabbage and carrots.
Mix other ingredients together.
Pour over cabbage until well coated.
Place in refrigerator to chill.
May also use red cabbage and 1 small grated onion.

title: sweet and dilly carrots
directions: Bring all ingredients, except carrots and garlic, to a boil in a large saucepan over medium heat.
Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Pack jars tightly with carrots and garlic.
Remove bay leaves.
Ladle hot liquid into jars to cover carrots. Refrigerate up to 1 month before serving.

title: heath bar candy
directions: Grease 10 x 15-inch pan.
Spread 1 1/2 cup chocolate chips on pan.
Melt oleo.
Add sugar, syrup and water.
Cook to hard crack stage.
Add nuts slowly; mix rapidly.
Spread over chips.
Top candy with 1/2 cup chocolate chips.
Soften and spread chips over candy.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup chopped almonds over top of chocolate. Cool completely and break up into small pieces.

title: old fashioned corn pudding
directions: Add all ingredients to corn.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake at 400° about 1 hour, until light brown.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Freeze in 2 (1 gallon) jugs and 1 (1/2 gallon) jug.
Remove from freezer about 1 to 2 hours before serving.
Mix 2 1/2 bottles of ginger ale to 1 gallon of mixture.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain.
Melt Cheez Whiz.
Put half of pepper and 1/2 can tomatoes in mixer and mix well.
Then put meat, cheese, peppers and tomatoes all together.
Pour over nachos.

title: butter pecan cake
directions: Mix cake mix and icing together.
Add eggs, oil and pecans. Pour into greased and floured tube cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Cream cottage cheese in bowl and add unbeaten eggs.
Cut or grate cheese and butter in pieces; add flour and stir.
Add defrosted broccoli and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: pillsbury cherry dream bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, 6 tablespoons margarine and 1 cup rolled oats. Mix until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup crumbs for topping. To remaining crumbs, add 1 egg and mix until well blended.
Press in pan.
Pour pie filling in and spread evenly.
To the reserved crumbs, add 1/4 cup oats, 2 tablespoons margarine, brown sugar and nuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Sprinkle over filling.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.
Cool completely.
If desired, serve with whipped cream.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Let sit overnight and enjoy.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Stir and mix well all ingredients except chicken.
Salt and pepper chicken.
Pour rice mixture into a 9 x 13-inch or larger pan.
Press chicken into rice mixture. Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 1 hour more. Keep covered while baking.

title: white chicken gravy
directions: Melt the Crisco. Stir in the Flour, Bouillon and Paprika. Stir in Water and Cream. Cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles. Cook 1 minute.

title: twist dish
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook and stir onion and pepper in the margarine until tender. Combine with the remaining ingredients. Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Freezes well.

title: blueberry streusel
directions: Mix together.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.

title: jerri's cheese roll
directions: Brown sausage; drain and pat dry with paper towels to remove all grease.
Cut cheeses into small pieces and melt together.
Add sausage.
Press into a mold and chill for 45 minutes.
Remove from the mold and serve.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Grease bowl.
Mix corn, egg, oleo and crumbled crackers.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 to 3/4 hour.

title: apple crisps
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Put sliced apples in a buttered 8-inch square baking pan.
Blend flour, oats, cinnamon, nutmeg and butter together until crumbly.
Spread over apples.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until topping is golden brown.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Use butter to keep from burning.
Simmer altogether and serve over rice or noodles.

title: no crust cheese pie
directions: Have cheese soft and beat in, gradually, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 375° until firm.
Remove from oven.
When cool, glaze with cherry pie filling.
Refrigerate.
May be served with whipped cream.

title: broiled frosting
directions: Mix together and spread over baked cake.
(I prefer German chocolate.)
Put under broiler for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: shrimp provencale
directions: Put 2 tablespoons oil in skillet.
Heat on medium heat; cook shrimp, stirring until pink.
Set aside.
Add 1 tablespoon more to the same skillet.
Add mushrooms and garlic; cook until mushrooms are tender, stirring occasionally.
Add tomatoes, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Cook 3 minutes more.
Return shrimp to skillet; heat.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve with rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: quick liver pate
directions: Thoroughly combine all ingredients.
Garnish with parsley.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Beat until fluffy.
Set aside.
Sift together flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Add dry ingredients to butter mixture, beating until thoroughly mixed.
Chill overnight.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix flour and sugar together; sprinkle over the drained pineapple.
Spread grated cheese over pineapple.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Pour melted butter over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt butter.
Add peanut butter; stir until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients; make into balls the size of large walnuts. Dip in chocolate.

title: pretzel-strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add strawberries and chill. Mix crushed pretzels with melted margarine and sugar.
Press pretzel mix into bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: aunt jacque's favorite punch
directions: Mix together in a punch bowl.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Combine first three ingredients; beat until light and fluffy. Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir vanilla into egg mixture.
Add flour mixture; beat.
Fold in apples, nuts and coconut.
Pour into greased and floured tube or flat pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, milk, vanilla, nuts, coconut and candied fruit.
Butter hands and roll mixture into small balls about 1/2-inch in diameter.
Place on cookie sheet and place in refrigerator to cool.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Sift flour and sugar together.
Add buttermilk and Crisco. Dissolve yeast in water and add to mixture.
Mix well.
Cover and let stand until dough is double in size.
Punch down; make into rolls of desired shape.
Let rise in warm place.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream the oleo and sugar. Add salt, well beaten eggs, syrup and nuts.
Mix well. Bake in raw pastry shell for 1 hour at 300°. (Use a 9-inch pie shell.)

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix well.
Decorate top with pecan halves.

title: peas vincenta
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in saucepan. Heat covered to boiling. Blend cornstarch and soy sauce in small bowl until smooth. Stir in peas gently. Cook over low heat until thickened, stirring constantly.

title: date nut chewies
directions: To toast pecans, bake on a cookie sheet at 350° for about 7 minutes.
Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 2 cookie sheets or line cookie sheets with greased foil.
Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Drop and shape by rounded tablespoonful 1-inch apart onto cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes or until cookies are browned around edges.
Cool on wire rack.
Store in an airtight container.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all together in mixing bowl.
Make into patties and fry in skillet with oil until brown and firm.

title: asparagus with anchovy and lemon
directions: Trim the ends off the asparagus.
In a saute pan, large enough to contain the asparagus lengthwise, bring to boil enough water to just cover the asparagus.
Add salt and cook asparagus until tender, but crisp.
Drain.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add egg yolks, one at a time and beat well after each addition.
Add lemon rind and juice. Add cheese and cream alternately with flour, mixing until smooth after each addition.
Fold in stiff beaten egg whites.
Sprinkle bread crumbs in well-buttered pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Add filling and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Chop the first 5 ingredients into small pieces.
Then mix with the mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Season lightly with garlic, pepper and salt, if desired.
Chill overnight.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add syrup and salt.
Beat well.
Blend in eggs, one at a time.
Flour pecans and add.
Pour into 9-inch pastry lined pie pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
I usually cover the edges with Reynolds Wrap so they don't get too brown.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Bake the first 7 ingredients for 15 minutes at 425°. Top with the last 4 ingredients. Bake an additional 15 minutes at 400°.

title: blueberry fantasy
directions: Bake cake as directed for 2 layers.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until thick.
Stir in zucchini squash, flour, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
Fold in nuts.
Pour in 2 greased and floured baking pans (8 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: pretzels
directions: Mix yeast, warm water, sugar and salt.
Sift flour.
Knead dough until soft.
Cut off lumps of dough (same size) and make into shapes.
Place on cookie sheet.
Brush with beaten egg and sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick. Add sugar, flour and salt.
Mix thoroughly. Slowly add boiling water.
Add vinegar and cook over double boiler until thick and smooth. Add lemon flavoring.
Pour into baked pie shell. Beat egg whites for meringue on top. Cook until brown.

title: 5 minute blender pumpkin pie
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender for 1 minute.
Pour into lightly oiled 10-inch pie pan.
Spread top with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and pepper.
Drain and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: virginia supper casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Rinse with hot water; set aside.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add beef. Cook until lightly browned.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.
Combine remaining ingredients in bowl; set aside.
Spread 1/2 of noodles in buttered 2-quart (12 x 8 x 2-inch) casserole and cover with 1/2 of cheese mixture.
Repeat.
Top with meat mixture.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Uncover; bake additional 10 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Mix together the crabmeat, lemon juice and cream cheese.
Add mayonnaise and herbs.
Stir well.
Bake 20 minutes in oven at 350° or microwave on High for 5 minutes.

title: "alice's restaurant" casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Cook onions, pepper, garlic and celery in oil. Do not brown.
Combine both and add tomatoes and chili powder. Cook noodles.
When almost done, drain and add to casserole. Layer noodles, meat and cheese. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: Boil unpeeled potatoes in enough water to cover them until tender.
When cool, peel and cube potatoes.
Mix with green pepper, grated cheese, onion, milk, salt and pepper.
Place in a large casserole dish and pour melted butter over all.
Sprinkle with fresh, chopped parsley.
Bake in preheated oven at 400°, approximately 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: marinated beans
directions: Drain about half of bean juice off and add all ingredients and mix well.
Tomatoes should not be added until about 1/2 hour before serving, but rest should be chilled overnight.

title: honey lime marinade
directions: Reserve 1/3 cup marinade and pour over barbecue grilled jumbo prawns.
Remainder of dressing goes over corn and bean salad.

title: furniture polish
directions: Mix and shake thoroughly.
Use like good furniture polish.

title: spice cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shirley bellmon's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add syrup and sugar to eggs and mix well.
Pour mixture into pie shell and sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal raisin spice cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour.
Mix well. Stir in oats, spices and raisins.
Mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Thoroughly mix in other ingredients. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° until pie shell is slightly brown.
Reduce heat to 300° and finish baking.
Bake pie approximately 40 minutes or so, until center is firm.
Cool before serving.

title: potato frank chowder
directions: Cook potatoes in water for 10 minutes, or until just tender. Slice frankfurters into 1/4-inch slices.
Saute with onion and celery in butter in large saucepan until vegetables are tender. Add soup, milk, salt, dill weed, potatoes and water.
Mix thoroughly.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and boil gently, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Makes 6 cups.

title: marinated roast
directions: Mix ingredients in glass baking dish. Add meat and turn occasionally.
Leave several hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours in the marinade and covered.
Remove meat from marinade.
If using for gravy, let cool and skim fat before heating to serve.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Place granulated sugar and cinnamon in a plastic bag.
Add biscuit pieces, a few at a time, and shake until each piece is coated.
Place in greased tube pan until all biscuit pieces are used up.
Sprinkle raisins and pecans in with biscuit pieces as you layer.
Bring brown sugar and butter to boil and pour over biscuit mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Allow to cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.
Turn upside down to serve.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Add yeast to potato water to dissolve.
In a good size bowl, put shortening, sugar, salt, mashed potatoes, milk and egg; beat well.
Add yeast and flour (enough for stiff dough).
Cover and let set overnight in refrigerator.
Take out for few minutes.
Roll out, place on pan.
Let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Bake in 400° oven. Will make about 60 rolls.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Strip cabbage of leaves and put in boiling water for a few minutes, until wilted down (don't overcook).
In heavy skillet, saute 1 cup of the onion in 4 tablespoons butter.
Place in mixing bowl.
Add beef, rice, 1 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper to taste. Mix together.
Lay cabbage leaves on work surface; place filling in center of each leaf and roll tightly.
Melt 4 tablespoons of butter and 2 tablespoons of oil.
Brown cabbage rolls and place in baking dish (single layer).
Melt remaining 4 tablespoons butter in skillet; add remaining onion and saute, then stir in tomatoes, 1 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Beat flour into sour cream.
Add this mixture to sauce.
Pour over rolls.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 325°.
Sprinkle with dill.
Serve cabbage rolls on bed of cooked noodles with dill as garnish.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: "after church" beef stew
directions: Put beef in 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with salt, basil and pepper.
Top with celery, carrots and onions.
Combine soup and water.
Pour over meat and vegetables.
Cover and bake at 300° for 3
hours.
Add potatoes and bake 45 more minutes.

title: red lobster stuffed mushrooms
directions: Use clean, fresh whole mushrooms with stems removed. Using 1/2 of crab cake mix, prepare according to package instructions, add canned crab meat (or imitation crab meat), mix well. Stuff mushrooms with mixture. Drizzle butter over them and cover with mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: mrs. field's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Using a large bowl, mix (on low speed) butter, brown sugar and white sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs and beat well.
In a separate bowl, mix flour, salt and baking soda.
Add the flour mixture to the sugar mixture.
The dough will become sticky and very dry so sometimes mixing with bare hands works best.

title: deep dish apple pie
directions: Place apples in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, 1/2 teaspoon of sugar and spices.
Sift potato flour, matzo meal and salt.
Beat egg yolks.
Add sugar and beat.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Fold into egg whites and spread over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Combine vegetables, toss lightly.
Combine remaining ingredients in a medium saucepan, bring to a boil over low heat. Stir occasionally.
Pour over vegetables, stir gently to blend well.
Cover, refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: english walnut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, syrup, melted margarine, cinnamon and vanilla.
Stir in walnuts; pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chicken-almond crepes
directions: Melt butter in medium skillet.
Add onion; saute until tender but not brown.
Blend in flour.
