Gradually stir in half and half. Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add chicken and sherry to half of the sauce.
Spread a heaping tablespoonful on each crepe.
Roll up and place in a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole. Cover with remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese and sliced almonds.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes, or until brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine everything but potato chips ahead of time.
Top with potato chips and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Yields 15 to 20 servings.

title: quick 'n easy chili pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spread chili. Mix cornbread in a separate bowl, according to directions on box. Spread cornbread mix evenly over chili.
Bake 25 minutes or until cornbread is done.
Serves six.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix cake mix, oil and eggs together, then add the chocolate chips.
Drop by tablespoon on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.

title: mildred's cornbread dressing
directions: Soak cornbread and biscuits in 4 cups stock, milk or water. Cook onion and celery in hot fat until golden.
Combine bread and onion mix with eggs, salt, pepper and poultry seasoning.
Add 4 cups stock to moisten.
Cook at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Boil chicken, pepper, celery, onion and bouillon until chicken is done.
Take chicken out.
Debone.
Use all of juice.
Fry sausage.
Put all together.
Put in long greased pan.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken broccoli oriental
directions: Cut chicken into strips.
In skillet, heat oil and cook 1/2 of chicken at a time, until brown.
Cut onion and pepper into 1-inch squares; add to chicken in skillet.
Cook until tender-crisp. Stir in soup, water and soy sauce; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: glogg nog
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and spices in mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed until sugar is dissolved.
Beat in ice cream and juices at low speed.
Chill covered until serving time.
Pour into punch bowl and add ginger ale slowly.
Fold gently to mix.
Float ice rings with orange slices in punch.
Garnish with nutmeg.
Yields 36 servings.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Grease cookie sheet lightly.
Beat egg whites, cream of tartar and salt in medium bowl until foamy.
Beat in sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Continue beating until stiff and glossy.
Do not underbeat.
Fold in almond extract and coconut. Drop mixture by teaspoonfuls about 1 inch apart onto cookie sheet. Place a cherry piece on each cookie.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or just until edges are light brown.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from cookie sheet.
Yields 3 1/2 to 4 dozen.

title: sandy's english muffins
directions: Add butter, salt and sugar to milk; cool to lukewarm.
Soften yeast in water; stir to blend well.
Add yeast, egg and 2 cups flour to cooled milk; blend well.
Knead in rest of flour until firm and elastic.
Let rise until double.
Pat out on floured board 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into 4-inch circles (I use a wide-mouth ring for my cutter.)
Put on a board sprinkled with cornmeal.
Let rise until double.
Fry in an electric frying pan sprinkled with cornmeal.
Fry slowly at 325° to 350° for 5 minutes on each side.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Crumble bread and milk, butter and salt. Heat on low until creamy.
Add salmon and eggs. Pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit-filled layered angel dessert
directions: Bake cake as directed; cool.
Trim brown crust from cake and discard.
Tear cake into 1-inch pieces.

title: crustless chicken quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 11 x 7-inch dish.
Combine chicken, broccoli, cheese and onion.
Mix remaining ingredients in blender.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: chocolate pudding frosting
directions: Whip until mixture stands in soft peaks.
Refrigerate for about one hour before frosting.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Combine pudding mix with 2 1/2 cups milk; set aside.
Break half of angel food cake into bite size pieces and place in large punch bowl or Tupperware container.
Pour half of pudding mixture over broken pieces of cake, then half of pie filling, half of pineapple and half container Cool Whip.
Repeat, ending with Cool Whip on top.
May garnish with cherries or sprinkle coconut on top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: oyster cracker appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour over crackers.
Stir until all liquid is absorbed and all crackers are coated.
Store covered.

title: no-kneading bread rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Put shortening, salt and sugar in separate bowl.
Add boiling
water.
Stir
until ingredients
are
dissolved.
When lukewarm,
add
yeast.
Add beaten egg.
Stir in flour to make a soft dough.
Chill
to 24 hours.
Top with butter before
refrigeration.
Rolls
will rise in 1 hour in warm place. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: *Make your own mix using 1/4 cup of flour, 1 1/2 teaspoons of baking powder, 1/4 teaspoon of salt, 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/2 cup cornmeal.

title: michelena's caramel squares
directions: Cut butter into dry ingredients until crumb mixture forms. Set aside 1 cup.
Press remaining crumbs into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Melt caramels and cream in top of double boiler.
Blend in flour.
Spread over cookie base. Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over caramel mixture.
Top with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Pour eggs into mixing bowl.
Beat in corn syrup, sugar, peanut butter, vanilla and salt until well blended.
Fold in pecans and chocolate chips, stirring well.
Pour filling into pastry shell. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Great served warm or cold!

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Heat margarine in 2-quart saucepan until melted.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until bubbly; remove from heat.
Stir in broth and milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole or oblong baking dish, 10 x 6 x 1 1/2 inches.
Cook, uncovered, in 350° oven until bubbly, 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dessert crust
directions: Mix well and put into a 9 X 12 pan.
Bake 12-15 minutes at 400°.
Cool slightly.
Then add:

title: crunchy chocolate cookies
directions: In a large bowl, mix the cake mix, butter and eggs.
Blend well, then add coconut, nuts, corn flakes, oatmeal and chocolate chips.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten each cookie with the bottom of a glass that has been dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until done.

title: chicken parmesan and spaghetti
directions: Mix milk and egg (make thin for dipping); set aside.
Mix the flour, salt, pepper and garlic; set aside.
Start water to boil for spaghetti.
Tenderize chicken breasts, then dip in flour mixture, then in egg mixture, then in flour mixture.
Fry until chicken is brown.
Dip chicken in Parmesan sauce.
Put the cooked spaghetti in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put Parmesan sauce over all. Cook until chicken is tender, then add Mozzarella and let melt. Put Parmesan sprinkles on top when all is done.

title: hot meat sandwich
directions: Make 4 meat sandwiches and place in 9 x 12-inch buttered cake pan.
Drain mushrooms and mix with 1 can of mushroom soup.
Add eggs and mix.
Pour over sandwiches.
Sprinkle on mushrooms and 1 cup of grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Peel and slice onions thin.
Cut cabbage coarsely.
Cook beef until browned and drain.
Add onions, cabbage and celery.
Cook until light brown.
Stir in tomatoes, beans with liquid, water, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat. Prepare dumplings with Bisquick and milk.
Drop by spoonfuls into boiling stew.
Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika and serve.

title: guacamole soup
directions: Cut avocados lengthwise into quarters.
Remove pits and peel. Mix avocados, water and milk in blender until smooth.
Thoroughly stir in lemon juice, seasoned salt and red pepper sauce.
Fold tomato into soup.
Chill.
If desired, garnish each serving with lemon slice.
Yields eight 1/2-cup servings.

title: rice pudding
directions: Stir sugar, rice and salt in a deep pan.
Add milk and stir in butter.
Place in preheated 400° oven.
Bake for 2 hours.
After first hour, stir every 15 minutes until pudding thickens.
Place in serving bowl, sprinkle with nutmeg and cool to room temperature before serving.

title: chicken corn chowder
directions: Melt butter in 3-quart saucepan.
Saute onion, celery, carrot and pepper.
Add flour.
Blend to make roux (5 to 10 minutes, do not brown).
Blend in chicken stock and bring to boil.
Add creamed corn and bring slowly to boil.
Add potatoes and simmer 15 minutes.
Add corn kernels, season and cook until potatoes are tender.
Add chicken and cream.

title: condensed milk
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and process until smooth. Keeps several weeks in
refrigerator.
Inexpensive and can be used in peas, salads, desserts, etc.

title: chili
directions: Fry onion and celery in a little butter or margarine very slowly, but do not brown.
Fry hamburger very slowly and do not brown.
Mix all together and cook slowly for 4 hours or more, after adding all other ingredients.
If too thick, thin with tomato juice.
Stir often so as not to burn.
This recipe will feed a crowd.

title: slaw
directions: For dressing, bring to boil water, sugar and vinegar, then add oil; bring to boil again.
Set off heat.
Add the mustard, mayonnaise, celery seed and salt.
I put in blender to mix.
Keep in refrigerator until time to pour over shredded cabbage a while before serving time.
Finely chopped carrot, apple, pineapple or green pepper may be added if desired.
I always get asked to bring this to dinners.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, water and seasoning.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
In baking dish, alternate layers of cooked noodles, sauce and cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Start with Velveeta cheese.

title: egg bake
directions: Brown sausage (set aside).
Break slices of bread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together the sausage, milk, eggs, dry mustard and 1 cup grated cheese.
Pour over the bread and add 1/2 cup grated cheese on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes.

title: congealed blueberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling water.	Cool and add pie filling and pineapple with syrup.
Whip cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Spread on top of congealed salad and refrigerate.

title: crab fondue
directions: Melt cheese then add crab meat and rest of ingredients.
Use as dip for Italian, French or other hard crust bread.

title: ruby's rolls
directions: Place flour in large pan; set aside.
Mix water, yeast, margarine, salt and sugar in another pan; stir until yeast is dissolved.
Put into flour and mix until it is in a ball.
Cover and let rise; punch down and let rise again.
Make little balls and let rise.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: zebra pie
directions: First Layer:
Combine softened margarine, flour and nuts. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool completely.

title: bootlegger beans
directions: Fry bacon; when about half done, add onion.
When onion starts to
brown,
pour
off
most
of
the grease and add the beans, brown sugar and ketchup.
Stir well, cover the pan with a lid and simmer very slowly for a few minutes.

title: pecan sandies
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat butter with an electric mixer on medium to high speed for 30 seconds.
Add about half of the flour, the sugar, vanilla and 1 tablespoon water.
Beat until thoroughly combined.
Beat in remaining flour.
Stir in pecans.

title: oatmeal cinnamon drops
directions: Cream together butter and sugar, add molasses, eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oats, raisins, nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 minutes, or until light brown.
Makes 6 dozen (recipe can be halved).

title: potato corn chowder
directions: Mash enough potatoes to equal 1/2 cup, then dice remaining potatoes; set both aside.
In medium saucepan, melt butter; add green onions and fry 1 minute.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Gradually add milk, stirring until smooth.
Cook, stirring over medium heat until thickened.
Stir in potatoes and corn.
Cook 6 minutes until thick.

title: sugar-free applesauce
directions: Put apples in kettle and add the 7-Up and spices.
Cook until the apples are very soft.
Chill.

title: microwave cheesecake(makes 9-inch cake)
directions: Beat cream cheese and 1/2 cup sugar in large mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg yolks, lemon juice and peel until smooth.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Cook last 4 ingredients to soft ball stage.
Pour over popcorn, stirring until all corn is coated.
Add peanuts, of course.
Place in preheated oven at 200° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Combine the first four ingredients.
Combine the next 3 ingredients.
Use long dish.
Spread bean dip on bottom and sides of dish, then spread sour cream mix.
Top with avocado mix. Sprinkle tomatoes, onions and olives on top.
Garnish with shredded cheese.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Scald milk; add sugar, shortening and salt.
Stir to melt sugar and shortening; cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Beat together cooled milk mixture, yeast, starter and 2 cups flour.
Add remaining flour to make a stiff dough.
Turn onto floured surface and knead 5 to 10 minutes, adding only enough flour to keep from sticking.
Place dough in greased bowl, turning to grease surface.
Let rise until doubled, about 1 1/2 hours. Punch down; let rise again, about 1/2 hour.
Divide into 2 balls. Cover with towel and let rest 10 minutes.
Shape into 2 loaves and put each in a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Let rise until doubled, about 1 hour.
Bake in 400° oven for 25 minutes.
Turn out and cool.

title: peanut butter crispy treats
directions: Melt corn syrup and peanut butter in microwave until peanut butter is completely melted. Stir every couple minutes. Mix in rice crispy cereal and let set until hardened.

title: delicious bavarian kraut
directions: Put kraut as it comes out of can in a large skillet; add 1 can water, minced onion, caraway seed and meat (cut as desired).
Add Equal.
Put lid on so flavor of meat and seed with kraut will blend.
Put on high heat until it starts to boil.
Turn heat down to simmer until most of water and juice is thoroughly blended. Cook for approximately 1/2 hour, until consistency is to your taste.
Add pepper, if desired.

title: italian roast beef
directions: Cook roast (uncovered) for 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Remove roast; add water, bouillon and seasonings.
Cover and bake at 250° for 3 1/2 hours.
May be served hot.
Make gravy using marinade. May be allowed to marinate in refrigerator.
When cool (or next day), slice and reheat to serve.
This makes great sandwiches or a main course.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly and pack firmly into a loaf pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy fruit crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spread pie filling in bottom of an 8 x 8-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with cake mix and drizzle with melted butter. Sprinkle with chopped nuts. Bake for 40 to 50 minutes. Makes 12 servings.

title: heavenly hash candy
directions: Cut marshmallows in half and spread on waxed paper so they won't stick together when you are ready to assemble candy.
Line lasagne dish with heavy foil.
Melt chocolate in large microwave bowl, 1 to 2 minutes on High.
Stop and stir, 3 minutes maximum, just to the soft stage (that you can stir) but not liquid.
Add marshmallows and mix well so they don't float on top of candy.
Add pecans.
Pour into dish and refrigerate 20 to 22 minutes maximum (just until firm).
Check periodically.
Turn upside-down on cutting board and peel off foil.
Cut in pieces.
Store in Tupperware.
Keeps at least a month.
One batch makes 75 pieces.

title: apple cider bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with cider to creamed mixture.
Stir in lemon juice, raisins and nuts.
Fold in apples.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Cool 10 minutes in pan and remove to rack to cool completely.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Boil cherries in water.
Cool slightly.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to thoroughly mixed mayonnaise/sugar mixture. Stir in cherries and water.
Add walnuts and vanilla. Pour into greased and floured 5 x 9-inch loaf pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 5 minutes.
Remove from pan and wrap in Saran Wrap or foil. Freezes well.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers (thin) and onions. Mix with salt. Let set 1 hour. Drain. Heat together remaining ingredients. Drop in drained cucumbers and onion slices. Heat through. Pack in jars and seal.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine flour, soda, sugar, salt and cinnamon in bowl; mix well. Add oil and eggs, stirring just until flour mixture is moistened. Stir in 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla, undrained pineapple, walnuts and bananas. Spoon into 3 greased and floured 9-inch layer pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake tests done. Cool in pans for 1 minute. Remove to wire racks to cool completely.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Drain liquid from corn into measuring cup; add enough cream or milk to measure 1 cup.
Heat butter; add flour, salt and pepper. Stir until blended.
Slowly add liquid and stir constantly until thickened.
Remove from heat and add drained corn.
Slowly add beaten eggs, stirring constantly.
Pour into greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Top with buttered crumbs and sprinkle with paprika.
Place in a shallow pan of water.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar,
cocoa,
milk
and
margarine
in
saucepan. Bring to boil over
medium
heat.
Remove from heat and cool 1 minute. Add vanilla,
salt, peanut butter and oats.
Mix well and drop by spoon on waxed paper.

title: bran muffins
directions: Melt Crisco in the boiling water in a small bowl.
Dissolve the baking soda in the buttermilk.
Add Crisco mixture and milk mixture in a very large bowl or pot.
Add the remaining ingredients and blend well.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.
This mixture can be kept refrigerated for 1 to 2 weeks.
Cooked muffins freeze well.

title: gazpacho
directions: Combine and chill for at least 2 hours.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts.
Form into a ball and then roll in chopped nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: ginger-nut chicken(microwave)
directions: Place
butter
in a 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Microwave at High for 45 seconds or until melted.
Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Add to casserole.
Coat with butter.
Cover and microwave
at
High
4 minutes, stirring after 2 minutes. Add broccoli,
onions,
celery and ginger root.
Microwave at High for 2 minutes.

title: taco chicken
directions: Combine milk, chicken soup, mushroom soup, onion, sour cream, olives, chilies and garlic salt in large mixing bowl.
Break taco chips into bite size pieces and cover bottom of casserole dish. Layer with chicken and soup mixture and cheese, starting with chips; repeat.
Bake until bubbly for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: corn flake macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites stiff and add sugar. Carefully add corn flakes, nuts, coconut and vanilla. Drop on greased pan and bake.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in greased baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Cut when cool.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix ingredients and stir 2 minutes.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°. Serve with Sauce.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Mix crumbled Oreos with butter and press firmly into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: beef and barley soup(crock-pot meal)
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Put all ingredients in a 4-quart slow cooker and stir.
Cook on high for 4 to 5 hours.
Or cook on high for 2 hours, then on low for 4 to 5 hours.
Or cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: sausage balls
directions: Allow sausage and Cheddar cheese to sit at room temperature; work into Bisquick, making a stiff dough.
Roll into small balls; bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Can be frozen.

title: strawberry torte
directions: Partially thaw strawberries.
In a medium mixing bowl, combine pudding with milk, mixing well.
Stir in Cool Whip and cake pieces. Spread mixture in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.

title: frosted strawberry punch
directions: Heat sugar, water and Kool-Aid until syrupy; cool.
Whip evaporated milk and lemon juice until 3 times original volume. Fold in Kool-Aid mixture and freeze.
Add ginger ale and strawberries to milk; freeze when ready to serve.
If thicker punch is desired, increase amount of milk freeze in proportion to ginger ale.

title: don's jambalaya
directions: In slow cooking pot first 9 ingredients.
Add water just above ingredients.
Cover and cook on low 4 to 5 hours.
Add shrimp. Cook until done.
Add rice or make a rice bed for mixture.

title: apple oat cake with fruit cream
directions: Core, quarter and steam apples for 10 minutes.
Place cooked apples and their juice in food processor and process to a sauce. Add honey, lemon juice, wheat bran and powdered milk to applesauce and process to mix well.
Add oatmeal to apple mixture and process to just fold in, being careful not to overprocess and lose texture.
Whip egg whites until stiff but not dry and fold apple mixture into whipped egg whites.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with nonstick spray and pour batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes to brown.
Cool cake, cut into 24 pieces and top with Orange Cream.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all three cheeses together with mixer.
Add mayonnaise, garlic salt, onion and walnuts to cheese mixture.
Shape into a ball and wrap with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.
When ready to serve, sprinkle with paprika.

title: fig cake
directions: Mix together and pour in cake pans and bake at 325° until done.

title: oatmeal buttermilk pancakes
directions: Add oats to buttermilk and baking soda.
Let stand 5 minutes. Mix together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add eggs and oil to oat mixture.
Make as regular pancakes.
Yield 14 to 16 pancakes.

title: frozen ambrosia
directions: Mix well and put in a large container for freezer or in several small containers.
Freeze overnight.
Will keep for weeks.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Blend sugar and cocoa.
Mix beaten eggs, butter, milk and vanilla.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in pie shell (unbaked).
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: luau pork roast
directions: Insert tip of knife into meat at even intervals and push garlic halves into meat as you remove knife.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain. Combine next five ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Stir in cooked broccoli and tabasco sauce.
Pour into greased 9x13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 25-30 minutes or until brown.
Yields 24 small squares.

title: artichoke appetizers
directions: Drain and squeeze liquid from artichoke hearts and chop them up.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Spoon over bread.
Place under broiler about 2 minutes or until brown.

title: caramel apples
directions: You will also need 6 wooden skewers.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes
and
drain.
Add all ingredients and mix well. Adjust
mayonnaise	to
consistency you want.
Place on platter and
garnish
with paprika.
For a festive look, place salad on lettuce or surround with deviled eggs.

title: georgia peach ice cream
directions: Place gelatin in small saucepan.
Pour 1/2 cup water on top and let soak for 5 minutes.
Heat over low heat, stirring, until dissolved.
Stir in remaining water.
Add condensed milk, half and half, vanilla and peaches to gelatin mixture.
Refrigerate for at least 3 hours.

title: pink salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; add sugar.
Chill until partly set.
Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Stir in whole milk. Combine cheese and Cool Whip with Jell-O and beat with beaters. Fold in nuts and pineapple.
Chill and serve.

title: weight watchers vegetable soup
directions: Cut up vegetables and cover with water.
Add onion soup mix and cook until done.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: To soften cream cheese, microwave 20 to 30 seconds in small microwave bowl (try Medium heat).
Add sour cream and taco seasoning.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Cover and refrigerate 2 to 4 hours to blend flavors.
Serve with tortilla chips or assorted raw vegetables.
Makes 3 cups.

title: spanish bars
directions: Add cold water to the raisins and boil 10 minutes.
Add the shortening and let cool.
Sift together the sugar, spices, flour and salt.
Add nuts and the cooled mixture.
Add the beaten egg and blend well.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350° in two 10 x 15-inch pans.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients with mixer and add margarine (melted), salt and cornstarch.
Cook slowly 1 hour and add 3/4 cup sugar. Simmer for 2 hours.
Recipe makes about 1 gallon.

title: taco soup
directions: Blend all together in a Dutch oven pan.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pat into loaf pan.
Top with can of tomato sauce.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: easy sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix last 3 ingredients together; pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients into blender for 30 seconds at low speed. Pour into ungreased 10-inch pie tin.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Cool, serve with Cool Whip.
Also good plain.

title: pork chops
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter until brown.
Add poultry seasoning.
Place pork chops in baking dish.
Add onions and celery.
Top with bread crumbs.
Add mushroom soup.
Bake at 350° until tender.

title: onion and pepper relish
directions: This is hot relish.
Combine all ingredients and bring to a boil; cook until slightly thickened, about 45 minutes, stirring on medium heat.
Pack into jars.
Process in hot water bath for about 10 to 15 minutes, counting when water in canner returns to boiling.
Remove jar and complete seals.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix together sugar, eggs, pumpkin and salad oil.
Sift dry ingredients and mix into pumpkin mixture.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: golden delight pancakes
directions: Put all ingredients into blender. Cover and blend at high speed for 1 minute, stopping to stir once. Bake on greased griddle using 1/4 cup batter per pancake.
Makes 20 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions on package.
Drain and rinse.
Put spaghetti in a large bowl with a tight fitting lid; add remaining ingredients and stir occasionally.
Let stand overnight, stir and serve.

title: kielbasa bean soup
directions: Peel and cube potatoes and carrots; peel and chop onion and slice celery.
Put in water and boil about 30 minutes.
Add soup and meat; simmer together about 15 minutes.

title: layered bean dip(serves 10 to 12)
directions: In a medium bowl, mix together refried beans, green chilies and taco seasoning mix.
Spread on a 12-inch round serving platter.
Blend avocados, lemon juice and 1/2 cup taco sauce until smooth.
Spread on top of bean mixture.
Top with shredded lettuce, cheese, taco sauce and olive slices.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: "jello punch"
directions: Put lemons in boiling water.
Let stand about 10 minutes; squeeze and strain juice.
Use water lemons were in as part of 4 quarts; dissolve sugar in hot water, also Jell-O and mix well. Add cranberry juice and pineapple juice.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Serves approximately 100.

title: pasta with broccoli and bacon
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Add bouillon cubes and whole garlic to broccoli. When broccoli is done, add bacon to it with about 3 tablespoons of bacon grease.
Simmer for about 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook pasta in boiling water.
When done, drain, reserving about 2 cups of the water.
Put pasta back in pan and add broccoli mixture and 2 cups of reserved water.
Heat through.
Serve with lots of grated cheese.

title: danish cookies #2
directions: Cream butter and lard.
Add sugar and cream together thoroughly.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients and sift in a little at a time.
Roll into small balls and flatten with fork. Bake in 350° oven until slightly brown.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: mama's tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar, eggs, vanilla and margarine.
Fold flour in slowly.
Roll thin and cut into shapes.
Cook at 350° until bottom is light brown.

title: mrs. fisher's cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: honey raisin bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Beat egg, margarine and honey in bowl.
Stir in flour mixture with milk and buttermilk just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in raisins and pecans.
Spoon in a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake in a slow oven at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Remove bread from pan onto rack.
Let stand overnight to slice.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook peas and carrots.
Drain; set aside.
In a saucepan, cook onions and mushrooms in butter until tender.
Stir in flour, salt, poultry seasoning and pepper.
Add chicken broth and milk at once. Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Stir in drained peas and carrots and chicken or turkey.
Pour mixture into round baking casserole.
Top with pastry (or substitute biscuits for pastry). Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes or until pastry biscuits are golden brown.
Yields 6 servings.

title: favorite garlic dressing for spinach salad
directions: Combine all ingredients
in a jar.
Now shake the jar vigorously!
Makes 1 1/4 cups dressing.

title: fruit compote
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan; stir well.
Drain pineapple, reserving 3/4 cup juice.
Add reserved juice and next 3 ingredients to cornstarch mixture, stirring until smooth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly. Combine fruit; pour hot glaze over fruit, gently stirring to coat.
Cover.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Garnish with grated orange rind.
Serves 8.

title: spicy chicken and rice
directions: Bake chicken breasts at 400° for 30 minutes. Cool.
In skillet, brown sausages.
Cool. Cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Set aside. Saute onion and green pepper in olive oil until tender. Add seasonings.
Stir in chicken, sausage, soup, tomatoes and rice.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Spoon into a buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese. Broil until cheese melts.

title: lucille's chess pie(yields 2 pies)
directions: Combine sugar, salt and flour.
Add butter, lemon, eggs and milk.
Beat slightly.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°, then reduce temperature to 250° and bake another 60 minutes or until done.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Cube bread.
Pour
melted
butter
over
bread and toss well. In buttered 9
x
13-inch
casserole
layer
bread cubes, 1/2 shredded cheese, 1/2 broccoli, all the ham, remaining broccoli, cheese and bread cubes.
Beat egg and milk.
Add seasoning.
Pour mixture
over
all layers.	Refrigerate overnight or at least 2 hours.
Bake until puffy and nicely brown at 350° for 40 minutes to 1 hour.

title: meltaways
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar and vanilla.
Sift flour, cornstarch and salt.
Add to butter mixture.
Fold in nuts and melted chocolate.
Shape into 120 balls using 1 teaspoon dough. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 40 minutes. Place on paper towel after baking.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix beans, soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Top with fried onions.
Make at 375° until browned on top.

title: squash delite
directions: Boil until done, squash, bacon and onion.
Drain and place in pot with butter and cream cheese.
Heat until melted and all mixed together.
Pour into a baking dish and cover with bread crumbs. Heat 5 to 10 minutes.
Ready to eat.

title: coke salad
directions: Combine water, sugar and cherries and boil gently for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in jello until dissolved.
Add pineapple (don't drain), nuts, and coke.
Place into mold and chill.

title: mashed sweet-potato caramel
directions: Mash potatoes with sufficient milk or cream to make smooth and moist.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place in a well-greased casserole or baking dish and pour in thick maple syrup which has been boiled with butter.
Bake in a moderate 350° oven until top begins to caramelize, 20 to 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk pecan candy
directions: Combine buttermilk, sugar, oleo, baking soda and syrup in a large kettle.
Cook to a soft ball stage, 235° to 240° on thermometer.
Cool slightly.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Beat until thick enough to pour in buttered dish.

title: briam
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cut up all vegetables.
Put into casserole dish.
Mix tomato paste with 1/4 cup water.
Pour over vegetables. Pour 1/2 cup oil over mixture.
Stir.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 2 hours.
Stir frequently.

title: french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in jar and shake.

title: country meat loaf(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine catsup, sugar and mustard; set aside.
In large bowl, combine remaining ingredients and 1/3 cup sauce; mix well.

title: fast 'n fabulous fudge
directions: Line an 8-inch square baking pan with plastic wrap.
In a 3-quart microwavable bowl, combine corn syrup and milk; stir until well blended.
Microwave on High (100%) for 3 minutes.
Stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Stir in powdered sugar, vanilla and walnuts.
With wooden spoon, beat until thick and glossy.
Spread in prepared pan.
Refrigerate 2 hours or until firm.

title: pecan chess pie
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In a medium bowl, mix sugars and flour. Fold in melted butter.
Beat eggs and fold into the first mixture. Next, add to mix, milk and vanilla.
Stir in pecans and pour into unbaked pie shell (9-inch deep) and cook for 45 minutes.
Makes 1 pie.

title: blue cheese rib eye steaks
directions: Combine cream cheese, Blue cheese, yogurt, onion and pepper; reserve.
Rub each side of steaks with garlic.
Grill to taste, seasoning with 1/4 teaspoon salt each side.
During last 5 minutes of grilling, top each steak with reserved cheese mixture. Garnish with parsley.

title: poor man's fruit cake
directions: Boil the first eight ingredients 5 minutes (no more)
Then add baking powder, baking soda, nuts and cherries.
Add enough flour (4 to 5 cups) to make a thick batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: maple syrup
directions: In medium pan place first 3 ingredients.
Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and cool.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Serve over pancakes or waffles.
Makes about 1 pint syrup.

title: *play dough
directions: Super-absorbent material, sold under the name "Water Grabber" is available from garden supply stores and can be found in the garden department of some variety stores.

title: cobbler busia
directions: Pour filling into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Crumble cake mix over the top. Drizzle melted butter on top. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: texas barbecue pasta sauce
directions: In large skillet heat oil.
Saute onion, green pepper and garlic until tender, but not brown.
Blend in remaining ingredients except pasta.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Serve sauce over hot cooked pasta.
Makes 6 servings.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup cool water and save.
Melt cheese and soup in saucepan.
Pour into mixing bowl.
Add gelatin and beat until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into lightly greased 6-cup mold.
Serve with crackers.
For 12 to 15 with cocktails.

title: looney tunes food
directions: There's green beans in there and surprises.
Those are games. There's carrots.
I know there are carrots in there because it's Bugs Bunny food.
I eat carrots, too.
There are mashed potatoes in there and ravioli and fruit.
You split 2 in half, and if there's more together, you have to split them in half.
Then you put one in the box, and you put another in a box.
Then you put the last one in the box, and it's done.
You have to look at the commissary or the store to see if it's done.
You buy it.
You bring it home for your dinner, and then you eat it.

title: crock-pot pork chops and potatoes
directions: Tear a piece of aluminum foil for each pork chop.
Place 1 chop on each piece of foil.
Season and add onion slices to each chop. Fold up foil loosely on each chop.
Stack in crock-pot. Pour in 1/2 cup water.
Add chunked and seasoned potatoes. Cover. Cook on low for 8 hours.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, then mashed bananas and remaining ingredients with flour being added last.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: spinach(quelites)
directions: Cook bacon and remove from skillet.
Saute onion in bacon drippings until transparent.
Drain off drippings.
Add bacon, spinach and beans and simmer over low heat for 10 minutes.
Serve immediately with hot flour tortillas.
Makes 4 to 6 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Beat eggs with fork; add to flour and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients, one at a time, mixing good. Put in unbaked pie crust and bake at 325° until golden brown and thick.

title: orange carrot salad
directions: *Can use 1/2 apricot and 1/2 orange jello.

title: impossible turkey pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a 10-inch pie plate. Sprinkle turkey, then mushrooms, onion, cheese and salt in pie plate.
Put remaining ingredients in blender or food processor; process 15 seconds until smooth (or beat in a bowl 1 minute with electric mixer).
Pour evenly over turkey and cheese.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until golden brown and knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Refrigerate any leftover pie.
Serves 8.

title: oh so good chicken
directions: Heat oil and saute green onions and mushroom; stir in chilis and salsa.
Cook and stir on medium heat for 5 minutes.
Place chicken in 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Cover with all but 1/2 c. of sauce.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: water-whip pie crust
directions: Place shortening in medium sized mixing bowl.
Add boiling water and milk and break up shortening with fork.
Tilt bowl and with rapid cross-the-bowl strokes, whip with fork until mixture is smooth and thick like whipped cream and holds soft peaks when fork is lifted.
Sift flour and salt together onto shortening mixture. Stir quickly, with round-the-bowl strokes, into a dough that clings together and cleans the bowl.
Pick up and work into a flat, round ball.
The dough is now ready to roll, either between waxed paper or on pastry cloth or lightly floured board.
Makes enough pastry for a 9-inch (2-crust) pie.

title: chicken-n-dumplings
directions: Judge for yourself on the amount of ingredients.
Mix the flour, water and eggs.
Salt and pepper the chicken while stewing it.
Knead the dough until it is stiff, then roll out the dough on a floured surface.
Roll it until it is very thin.
Then cut into small squares and put in pot of chicken by layers.
Cook each layer about 2 minutes apart to avoid sticking and gumminess.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes, combine with butter, salt and pepper.
Add onion, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Turn into 2-quart casserole.

title: christmas breakfast
directions: Take crust off bread and cut into cubes.
Grease 7 1/2 x 12-inch casserole and mix bread and cheese.
Beat eggs and milk; stir in seasonings.
Then pour over bread and cheese. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 minutes. This will puff up but fall outside of oven.

title: overnight salad
directions: Prepare pudding mix as directed on package.
(You may use whole eggs rather than just the yolks.)
Mix in lemon juice and cool. Fold in whipped cream.
Add to cream mixture.
Add fruit cocktail and marshmallows, stirring gently until blended.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cheese balls
directions: Cream all ingredients together.
Be sure they are mixed well. Form into a ball and roll in chipped beef, parsley or pecans.

title: zucchini cracker toppers or dips
directions: Simmer onion, zucchini, tomato sauce and hot pepper sauce for 15 to 20 minutes.
Put in blender container with cream cheese; blend until very smooth.
Stir in chopped dill pickle.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Mix together and melt over low heat on stove.
Store in refrigerator.
Keeps for long time.
Add 2 tablespoons per cup; jigger of rum and fill large cups with hot water (mug size cup).

title: impossible pie
directions: Combine.
Pour everything in blender.
Put in buttered pie plate.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: date bars
directions: Mix in order given and bake in an 8 x 8-inch baking pan at 275° (a slow oven) about 1/2 hour.

title: pickled beets - eggs
directions: Put beets and juice in a pan.
Add vinegar, sugar, salt and cloves.
Heat until sugar dissolves.
Cool.
Cook and shell eggs. Put in jar or bowl; pour beets over eggs.
Add water to bring juice over eggs.
Marinate 2 to 3 days, stirring several times.

title: pasta sauce "california style"
directions: Heat oil in a 3-quart saucepan or skillet with high sides. Add diced tomatoes.
Cook, covered, over medium heat for about 15 minutes or until tomatoes are soft.
Add parsley flakes or basil, garlic powder, sugar and tomato paste. If sauce is not liquid enough, add tomato puree to reach the desired consistency.
Just before serving, stir in salt.
Garnish pasta with fresh grated Parmesan cheese.

title: brandon's milkshake
directions: Put ice cream in blender; add milk and blend well.
Pour into your favorite glass.
Sit back and enjoy.

title: cheese straws
directions: Let cheese and margarine soften overnight at room temperature. Mix together until blended.
Gradually blend in flour, salt and cayenne pepper to form a soft dough.
Fill cookie press with dough.
Using the star design, form 2-inch straws on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with paprika.
Cool on paper towels.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, vanilla and salt with mixer.
Pour into freezer can, then add milk to fill line.
Freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: easter loaf
directions: Mix sugar, milk and Karo until well blended.
Cook to soft ball stage, stirring constantly with wooden spoon.
Remove from heat. Beat by hand or with electric mixer until mixture cools.
Add fruits and nuts.
Pour into pan lightly greased with butter.
Cut into squares when candy begins to get firm.
Store in refrigerator.

title: lemon grilled salmon
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients. Sprinkle over salmon and place in a reclosable bag. Place in a shallow glass container. Combine rest of ingredients. Pour over salmon and place in refrigerator at least 1 hour. Remove from bag and place on tinfoil. Cover with thinly sliced lemon and onions and wrap in foil, skin side down. Grill over medium heat 15 to 20 minutes until fish flakes. Enjoy.

title: animal cookies(old family recipe)
directions: Blend sugar and Crisco.
Add buttermilk, eggs, baking powder, soda, salt, vanilla and flour until stiff.
Roll out; cut into cookies.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Use your favorite icing recipe and favorite sprinkles.
I always let my girls and now grandchildren put their icing on and sprinkles (making memories).

title: 2 pie crusts with oil
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients then add 3 tablespoons cold water and mix again.
Shape into ball.
Divide.
Dampen counter or board. Place each ball between 2 sheets of wax paper and roll to fit pan. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: delicious pumpkin pie
directions: * Will make 2 large pies.

title: lois' eggplant parmigiana(main dish and excellent for sandwiches, hot or cold.)
directions: Use your favorite tomato sauce.

title: blackberry pie
directions: Fill bottom crust heaping with blackberries. Sprinkle with flour, salt and sugar. Dot with small pieces of butter. Cover with top crust or strips of pastry across top. Bake about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: special chicken
directions: Grease casserole with butter.
Line bottom with dry beef. Place chicken slices on top.
Mix soup and sour cream together; add fresh mushrooms.
Spread on top of chicken.
Cover dish with foil; place in refrigerator overnight to saute.
Before baking, let casserole set at room temperature for 1/2 hour.
Bake, covered, at 250° to 275° for 3 hours.
Check while baking. Uncover last 30 to 45 minutes to brown.
Good served with rice or buttered noodles.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Brown chicken.
Drain off all excess oil.
Mix ingredients well and pour over chicken pieces.
Cover and simmer until chicken is done.
Serve over rice or egg noodles.
Is also good over cornbread.

title: beef stew
directions: Put all ingredients into a casserole with a tight cover.
Bake for 5 hours at 250°, stirring occasionally, or put all ingredients into your crock-pot on low for 8 to 10 hours.

title: chicken bake
directions: Place chicken in large baking dish.
Sprinkle with rice.
Mix soups and water.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: raspberry meringue
directions: To the cracker crumbs, add the walnuts.
Beat egg whites with salt; when stiff, gradually beat in sugar.
Add lemon extract and vanilla.
Fold in crumbs and nuts.
Bake in buttered 9-inch pie pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Serve in wedges topped with raspberries (frozen) and juice and whipped cream.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix altogether.
Refrigerate for a bit for better taste. (This recipe makes a lot, so you may prefer to use 1 small package of cream cheese.
I do.)

title: pepper steak
directions: Pound steak and cut in strips.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Brown in butter.
Add garlic and bouillon cubes; cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir in onions and green peppers.
Cook 5 minutes more. Blend cornstarch, soy sauce and water.
Stir into meat mixture. Cook, stirring, until clear.
Add tomatoes.
Heat until warm. Serve over rice.

title: deep sea delight
directions: Cook noodles in salted, boiling water.
Rinse in cold water; drain.
Mix other ingredients in a bowl (keeping out enough cheese to sprinkle on top).
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: seven flavor precious chicken
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir together 1 tablespoon each of soy sauce, sesame oil and cornstarch.
Add chicken and let stand 10 minutes.
Break linguine in half and cook according to package directions.

title: simple homemade ice cream
directions: Place above ingredients in quart size freezer bag.
Place ice in 4 tablespoons of table salt in gallon size freezer bag.
Place smaller bag inside larger bag and shake for 5 minutes.

title: black cake
directions: Rub butter and sugar together and add yolks of eggs.
Add part of the flour and spices.
Fold in whites of eggs, well beaten, then remainder of flour and wine and brandy.
Mix all thoroughly.
Cover bottom and sides of 4-quart milk pan with buttered white paper. Put in a layer of mixture, then a layer of fruit which has been dredged with flour, until pan is filled up to 3/4 inch.
Bake 3 1/2 to 4 hours in slow oven.

title: corn pudding
directions: To the corn, add flour and sugar.
Mix well.
Beat eggs well and add milk.
Stir the 2 mixtures together.
Add butter, which has been melted in a baking pan.
Bake until golden brown (about 45 minutes at 350°).

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except potato chips.
Place in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with potato chips.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: willie's cabbage soup
directions: Cook everything together; add cabbage after everything is almost done.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into two 9-inch pie shells. Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 375° oven.

title: bean and carrot salad
directions: Mix all together and serve.
Contains 83 calories per serving.

title: peggy and delores' chocolate pie
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, flour and salt together thoroughly.
Add Carnation milk; stir until it starts to thicken some, then add egg yolks.
Blend all together.
Stir constantly until thickens as you like (in double boiler).
Take off heat; add vanilla and margarine.
Mix well.
Pour into two 9-inch baked pie shells.
Add meringue.
Cook at 300° until topping browns.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix together everything except cake mix, margarine and nuts. Pour in ungreased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over pumpkin mixture.
Pour on the melted butter.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: grandma rita's apple cake
directions: Mix better and sugar; add beaten egg.
Mix together the baking soda, flour and spices and add to above creamed mixture.
Stir in diced apples, nuts, raisins and vanilla.
Pour into greased 8x8x2 inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped topping, warm or cold, or your favorite ice cream.
It can be frozen.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together, add yolks of eggs.
Mix well. Put
soda
in
milk
and add to other ingredients.
Sift flour and
spices
together.
Add
to butter mixture.
Fold in beaten egg whites and add jam, nuts and raisins last.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) pans at 375° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: mom's chocolate candy oatmeal cookies
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter, add milk and mix well. Gradually add sugar, stirring constantly.
Add cocoa and stir until smooth and creamy.	Bring to a boil and cook for 1 minute.	Add vanilla and gradually add oatmeal and vigorously stir until batter starts to get firm.
Using a tablespoon, drop on wax paper lined cookie sheet to harden.
Put in refrigerator to harden.

title: chili-corn casserole
directions: Beat eggs, corn, oil, salt, garlic salt and cornmeal together in bowl with hand mixer.
Pour half corn mixture into greased 1-quart casserole.
Layer chiles and cheese over corn mixture. Top with remaining corn mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until casserole tests done.
Yields 4 servings.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Brown sausage.
Add onions, green pepper, bread crumbs and stems.
Stuff mushrooms with mixture; sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Put in oven at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Cream together shortening and peanut butter.
Gradually add white sugar and firmly packed brown sugar.
Cream well.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Blend in flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Shape into small balls and roll in white sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and place solid milk chocolate candy kiss on top of each cookie, pressing down so that cookie cracks around the edges. Return to oven; bake 2 to 4 minutes longer.

title: mom's divinity
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water until mixture dropped in cold water turns to brittle.
Pour slowly over stiffly beaten egg whites.
Add vanilla.
Drop firmly with spoon and top with half pecans.

title: date nuts bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, beaten separately. Add dates, nuts, flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Fold egg whites (stiffly beaten) in last.
Spread thin into 9 x 1-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut in strips while warm and roll in powdered sugar.

title: tuna-chicken-turkey casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana split sundae
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add cracker crumbs to melted margarine; put in pan.
Add sliced bananas and drained pineapple. Add milk to pudding and layer on top of pineapple.
Mix Dream Whip as package directs and put on top of pudding.
Add nuts and cherries on top.
Refrigerate.

title: country ribs and sauerkraut
directions: Heat oil and butter in Dutch oven over medium heat.
Brown ribs.
Add garlic and cook with ribs until golden brown.
Remove ribs.
Saute onion in drippings until tender. Add caraway seed, sauerkraut, red pepper, broth and salt and pepper to taste and brown sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from stove and top with apples and ribs.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 to 3 hours or until pork is tender.
Stir in carrots during last 10 minutes of baking.

title: blackened tuna steaks
directions: Chill tuna.
Melt margarine and dip.
Cover steaks well.
Cover with Cajun spice.
Heat pan for five minutes.
Preferably use iron skillet and get the pan hot.
Cook steaks until "scorched," not burned, approximately five minutes on each side.
Tuna is done when still slightly pink on inside; overdone if gray on inside.

title: easy pot roast
directions: Brown beef in hot oil in a 5-quart Dutch oven.
Add soup mix and water; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 4 hours. Vegetables may be added (potatoes, carrots and onions) if desired after 3 hours.
You cannot overcook this beef.
Add water, if necessary, during cooking.
I make gravy by adding flour mixed with water to liquid after removing meat.

title: deer chili
directions: Brown deer burger and onions together.
Add chili with beans and tomato sauce.
Add cooked macaroni and spaghetti.
Season to taste with chili powder and let simmer for about 15 minutes.

title: apple oatmeal cookies
directions: In medium bowl, combine first 7 ingredients.
Mix well with wire whisk.
Set aside.
Cream sugar and butter in a large bowl with electric mixer.
Add egg, applesauce and honey and beat at medium speed until smooth.
Add flour mixture, apple and raisins and blend thoroughly.
Do not overmix.
(Dough will be quite soft.)
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet (1/2-inch apart).
Bake 23 to 25 minutes or until bottoms are golden at 300°.

title: rhubarb delite
directions: Blend the first 3 ingredients.
Press into an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Cook the rhubarb, 1 1/4 cups sugar, 2 tablespoons flour, egg yolks and whipping cream over low heat until thick, stirring regularly.
Pour on cooled crust.
Use the 3 egg whites to make meringue.
Put meringue on hot ingredients; seal edges.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and taco mix with mixer until smooth and spread on tray.
Top with next 6 ingredients.
Add salsa and serve with taco chips.
Ideas for toppings are endless.

title: v-8 vegetable juice
directions: Cook tomatoes
in their own juice and run through sieve to remove
peel
and
seeds.
Cook together the celery, onions and peppers in the 5 cups water until tender, then run through blender.
Add
salt,
vinegar,
sugar,
vegetable
mixture
to tomatoes and
mix
well.
Bring to a rolling boil and put into sterilized jars and seal while hot.
Yields 9 quarts.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant in boiling water until tender.
Drain and add salt, bell pepper, black pepper, onion and tomatoes.
Add eggs and bread crumbs.
Pour into a 2-quart dish (greased), top with cheese and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp fettuccine
directions: Saute vegetables in butter. Add parsley, garlic and shrimp. Cook 10 minutes. Add flour and mix well. Add half and half and cheese.
Cook until smooth. Season to taste and simmer 30 minutes. Boil noodles and add to the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to package.
Saute onion and celery in butter.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place in casserole dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Very tasty!

title: nappa cabbage salad
directions: Cut up the onions and cabbage and chill.
Stir oleo, sesame seed, slivered almonds and Ramen noodles until brown. Cool.
Next mix and boil for 1 minute the vinegar, sugar, oil and soy sauce. Cool. Toss with cabbage. Toss ingredients just before serving.

title: becky's bread recipe
directions: Put the water, sugar, salt and shortening in mixing bowl.
Mix and then add eggs and mix well.
Add yeast to flour and begin adding to liquid mixture.
Change to dough hooks before adding last half of flour.
Mix at highest speed with dough hooks for 6 to 10 minutes.
Drizzle 1 teaspoon of oil around edge of dough for the last minute of mixing.
Dough will begin to pull away from edge of the bowl.
Place dough in a well-greased bowl.
Put in warm place until double in size.
Shape into loaves or hot rolls. Let rise again until double in size.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: hot pickled wieners
directions: Boil together, except vinegar.
Pour vinegar over wieners and peppers.
Set 3 days.
This recipe will serve 10 people.

title: fried squash
directions: Rinse squash and slice into chips, then add salt and pepper. Crack egg and separate yolk from white (use whites only).
In a large bowl, dip squash chips in egg white, then cover chips with flour.
Heat oil in skillet on medium to medium-high and cook until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: gore tomato relish
directions: Cook for 1 hour.
Stir often to keep from sticking.
Pour in sterilized jars and seal.

title: linzer torte
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan.
Sift flour and salt together.
Work butter in bowl until creamy; add sugar and beat well.
Add egg yolks and beat until blended.
Gradually add flour and mix until well blended.
With fingers pat about 2/3 dough evenly over bottom and sides of prepared pan.
Cover with raspberry jam.
Roll small amounts of the remaining dough with fingertips on a well floured board into strips 1/2-inch in diameter.
Lay strips of dough crisscross over jam about 1 1/2-inches apart.
Dough is very tender and may break when placing on jam.
If this happens, pinch ends of strips together to patch.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool and cut into bars before removing from pan. Makes about 3 dozen bars.

title: double peanut cookies
directions: Blend butter and sugar; add eggs and beat.
Sift and add flour, soda and salt.
Add oatmeal, vanilla and chips.
Drop by tablespoon onto cookie sheet and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: corn souffle
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: zesty barbecued ribs
directions: In a large pan, cook ribs in boiling water, 1 hour or until tender.
Meanwhile, in a medium saucepan, combine all remaining ingredients; simmer uncovered 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Grill or broil ribs as desired, turning and basting frequently with sauce.
This will serve 4 hungry people.

title: old fashioned lentil soup(serves 6)
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Boil the 7 1/2 cups water.
Add all ingredients but spices.
When rolling boil, add seasoning and simmer 20 minutes.
May puree 1/2 of soup mixture to thicken.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add 1 teaspoon of butter to taste.

title: pooh pooh's cake
directions: Combine cake ingredients. Beat at medium speed for two minutes. Pour 2/3 batter into streusel or pound cake pan that has been greased and floured. Sprinkle with streusel filling. Spoon remaining batter over filling. Bake at 375° until done. May glaze with mixture of 1 cup powdered sugar and 1 to 2 tablespoons milk.

title: sausage and cheese souffle
directions: Lightly grease an oblong casserole dish.
Place bread cubes in bottom of dish in a single layer.
Sprinkle sausage and mushrooms on bread; top with cheeses.
Combine eggs, half and half and spices.
Pour over all; refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: Cook noodles.
Drain in colander and keep warm.
Heat butter in saucepan until melted.
Add garlic and saute.
Stir in cream. Heat until hot, about 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in grated cheese, parsley and pepper.
Arrange noodles on platter. Pour sauce over noodles and toss.
Garnish with fresh parsley.

title: cherry angel dessert
directions: Place cake cubes in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Reserve 1/2 can cherry pie filling; spoon rest over cake.
Combine pudding mix, milk and sour cream; beat until smooth.
Spoon over cake.
Garnish with the remaining cherries and chill at least 5 hours.

title: gran's southern potato soup
directions: In large pot, cook first 5 ingredients in enough water to cover potatoes.
Cook until tender.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Make a soft dough by stirring 2 beaten eggs, 1/8 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper into 2 tablespoons of water.
Add enough flour to form a soft dough.
Pinch small bits of dough off and drop into soup.
Let soup come to a boil.
If desired, more milk may be added.

title: hot buns
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Add other ingredients.
Gradually add flour until stiff.
Knead.
Let rise.
Make into buns.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: savory crescent chicken squares
directions: Heat oven
In medium bowl, blend cream cheese and margarine until smooth.
Add next 6 ingredients. Mix well. Separate dough into 4 rectangles; firmly press perforations around edges together to seal.
Spoon 1/2 cup meat mixture onto center of each rectangle.
Pull 4 corners of dough to top of center of chicken mixture; twist slightly and seal edges.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle crouton crumbs on top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: baked west virginia ham
directions: Wrap
ham
in
foil or brown wrapping paper.
Place fat side up
in
roaster
and
bake
in slow oven, about 300°, 25 minutes per
pound.
Take
from
oven 45 minutes before done. Remove paper and rind.
In a bowl, mix 1 1/2 cups brown sugar, mustard
and white vinegar.
Rub into and all over ham, using all the mixture.

title: brownie pizza pie
directions: Grease and flour a 12 x 1/2-inch pizza pan.
In a 3-quart saucepan, bring corn syrup and whipping cream to boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Add chocolate; stir until melted. Set aside 2/3 cup of this chocolate sauce.
Add butter and sugar to the remaining sauce; stir until butter melts.
Remove from heat.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Gradually stir in flour, salt and nuts.
Pour into the pan.
Bake in 350°
oven for 20 minutes, or until firm; cool on rack.
Top with ice cream, fruit, nuts and chocolate sauce.

title: lemon gooeys
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and melted butter.
Press into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and 2 eggs. Mix on medium speed until creamy.
Spread on top of cake mixture. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Wash and prepare cabbage by chopping into large pieces and placing in bottom of a greased baking dish.
In a large skillet, brown meat and onion.
Drain; add rice and blend thoroughly. Season to taste.
Pour meat mixture over cabbage.
Cover with tomato soup and 1 cup water (use more water if dry soup mix is used).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: plain pastry
directions: Sift together flour and salt.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender until pieces are size of small peas.
Add water, one tablespoon at a time.
Toss with fork until all is moist.
Gather up to form ball.
On lightly floured surface, roll to 1/8-inch thick.
Place in pie pan.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Great as a marinade for steak, chops or a roast.
Marinate overnight.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa in a medium saucepan.
Add egg yolks, milk, vanilla and margarine.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.
Bake in 350° oven until golden brown.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Mix in a large, deep container.
Store in airtight container.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender; drain and cool.
Cook broccoli until just tender and drain (I steam it).
Combine mayonnaise, soup, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Bone and shred chicken and place in bottom of buttered pan.
Lay cooked broccoli side by side on chicken.
Pour sauce over all evenly.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: pasta salad-italian style
directions: Boil, drain and cool pasta.
Chop vegetables and olives and mix into pasta.
Chop meats and cheeses and add to pasta, mixing well.
In a separate bowl or jar, combine Vinaigrette dressing with mayonnaise; mix well.
Stir this mixture into pasta salad. Mix and add extra dressing, if needed.
If making this in advance, do not add scallions until you are ready to serve it.
Homemade Italian dressing with fresh chopped basil leaves works especially well with this recipe.

title: chocolate covered peanut butter crackers
directions: Sandwich two snack crackers together with a generous amount of peanut butter. Press together so peanut butter spreads to edge. Using tongs or a fork, dip crackers into melted chocolate coating. Can use a small bowl and melt enough chocolate to get about 1/2 inch deep. Be careful to microwave slowly, stirring every little bit until creamy.

title: deep dish apple dessert
directions: Place half the apples in a greased baking dish and pour corn syrup over apples.
Add remaining apples.
Mix remaining ingredients and press firmly over apples.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until apples are tender.
Desired spices to taste may be added with apples.

title: grilled baked cod
directions: Prepare coals and cover the grill with foil.
Grill the cod over hot coals for 5 to 6 minutes.
Turn and grill an additional 2 to 3 minutes or until fish flakes with a fork.
Serve with parsley and lemon wedges.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together and put in pan.
Bake 1/2 hour at 325°.

title: lucy's brunswick stew
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain well.
Mix remaining ingredients in food processor for only a short time, until well blended.
Blend small amounts at a time, then place in crock-pot to simmer all day.

title: fruit cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Drain and squeeze pineapple and cherries; chop in food processor.
Mix all ingredients (except pecans) and roll in chopped pecans.

title: ramen noodle salad
directions: Grate or chop cabbage.
Chop green onions.
Crumble Ramen noodles.
Combine in bowl.

title: house plant fertilizer
directions: Dissolve all in 1 gallon water.
Water plants with this every six weeks.

title: scalloped squash bake
directions: Cook squash in 1/4 cup water until tender.
Drain well.
In medium pan, cook onion and garlic in butter until tender.
Stir in flour and pepper.
Gradually stir in milk, bouillon, and oregano. Cook until thickened.
Remove from heat and add 1/2 of the grated cheese.
Combine with zucchini and pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onion rings and return to oven for 3 minutes.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Combine butter and bread crumbs.
Stir to coat crumbs.
Mix 1/2 the crumbs with remaining ingredients.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Cover with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes or until browned.

title: cool, creamy dressing
directions: In a blender or food processor, puree the cottage cheese, milk, lemon juice, mustard and garlic until smooth.
Transfer to a bowl.
Stir in the parsley and basil (another herb may be used for variety).
If too thick, thin with skim milk or non-fat yogurt.

title: creamed tacos
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain any fat.
Pour into a saucepan and add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Simmer until cheese is melted.
Serve over Fritos or Doritos.

title: apple muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

title: potato pie
directions: Mix all
ingredients
and
bake in prepared crust for 5 minutes at 425°; then bake at 350° until done.

title: ham sauce
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and heat over low heat. When mixture begins to bubble add cinnamon and cloves. Simmer on low 30 - 40 minutes. Cool and serve with ham.

title: brownie candy cups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place thirty 2-inch foil cup cake liners in small muffin pans or on cookie sheet.
Combine brownie mix, fudge packet, eggs, water and oil in large bowl.
Stir with spoon until well blended, about 50 strokes.
Place 2 level tablespoons of batter in each foil cup cake liner.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and push 1 peanut butter cup candy in center of each cup cake until even with surface of brownie.
Bake for 5 to 7 minutes longer.

title: six layer dinner
directions: Lightly oil baking dish; place ingredients in the order given in layers in a 8 x 12-inch pan, sprinkling salt and pepper over layers.
Bake for 2 hours at 350°.
Yield:
6 servings. Carbohydrate 15 g, protein 16 g, fat 11 g, calories 223.
One serving = 2 meat medium fat exchange, 1 bread starch exchange.

title: pasta salad
directions: Combine cooked rotini and 1/4 cup Italian salad dressing. Toss gently. Cover and chill. Combine red pepper strips and remaining ingredients. Add chilled rotini and toss gently. Serve salad chilled.
Makes 5 cups.
Contains 121 calories per 1 cup serving.
tags: commercial reduced calorie Italian salad dressing

title: grandma's heavenly pink salad
directions: Cream the cherry juice and cream cheese together.
Add cherries, bananas, pineapple, cool whip and marshmallows. Refrigerate.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Grease well and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Heat oven to 350°. Do not use electric mixer.
Mix by hand.

title: muffins
directions: Cook raisins in warm water.
Set aside to cool and drain. Beat oleo, brown sugar, white sugar till creamy. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat 30 more seconds.
Add buttermilk or yogurt. Mix for 1 min.
Add flour, soda, powder, salt and vanilla.
Mix well. Add bran, raisins, carrots and chocolate chips last.
Put in greased muffin pan and bake 400° for 15 mins.
If using large pans, bake for 20 mins. This dough keeps in refrigerator for 6 weeks.

title: hot fruit casserole
directions: Drain all fruit.
Combine oleo, sugar and flour; cook in double boiler until smooth.
Pour over fruit.
Keeps well in refrigerator for days.
Before serving, cook for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate cinnamon raisin bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Beat in egg.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Turn into a greased 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mary's rhubarb cake
directions: Place rhubarb, marshmallows and 1 cup sugar in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan, greased.
Beat 1 cup sugar and shortening together.
Combine eggs, milk, flour and baking powder with shortening-sugar mixture.
Pour over rhubarb.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sausage cocktail squares
directions: Cook sausage.
Pour off grease.
Put sausage on paper towels and knead with hands to get as much grease out of sausage as possible. Melt cheese and sausage together.
Spread on rye bread. Freeze in layers.
Before serving, bake 8 minutes at 400°.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Mix 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, garlic salt, egg and milk with cooked and drained spaghetti.
Put into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.
Remove from oven; spread tomato sauce over top.
Sprinkle 3 cups Mozzarella cheese on.
Add sliced pepperoni.
Return to oven and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: brownies
directions: Mix melted
butter and chocolate.
Combine sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Add
butter
and chocolate mixture.
Sift flour, salt and baking	powder;
add
to other mixture.
Add nuts and chocolate morsels.	Bake in
a
9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: soaking solution to get spots and mildew out of clothing* * * * * *
directions: A little baking powder added to meat loaf will make it more fluffy and if you add about 1/2 cup milk to a pound of hamburger, let it set for 1 to 1 1/2 hours before using it; it will be more juicy.

title: holiday appetizer pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and milk, then stir in all but walnuts. Spoon in 8-inch pie plate or shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle walnuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: dissent
directions: Mix together and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°f. 180°c. gas mark 4 for 15-20 minutes.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Combine apple cider with ginger ale in a 30-cup percolator. In the basket of the percolator, put red hots, whole cloves and cinnamon sticks.
Perk as you would coffee.

title: taco salad
directions: Break lettuce into pieces.
Cut tomatoes into wedges.
Rinse and drain pinto beans.
Mix ingredients together and enjoy!

title: homemade peach ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Pour into ice cream churn. Churn until set.
Makes 1 gallon of ice cream.

You can substitute peaches with other fruit; such as bananas (3 large), pineapple (one medium can, crushed), strawberries (two cartons, frozen) or make chocolate (pour chocolate syrup in until it looks rich enough for your taste).
Yum, yum!

title: linguine salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and refrigerate overnight.

title: baked fish with mushrooms
directions: In a skillet, cook bacon; reserve drippings.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Cook mushrooms and onions in drippings until tender. Place fish in a baking dish; sprinkle with salt.
Combine mushrooms, onion, butter and tarragon.
Spread atop fish; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until fish flakes with fork.
Garnish with the crumbled bacon.
Makes 4 servings.

title: flan cake
directions: Make cake as per box directions. Mix together all ingredients (except fruit). Spread on cake when cool and top with fruit.

title: texas caviar
directions: Combine all ingredients except dressing.
Mix well.
Pour dressing over and mix well.
Cover and marinate at least 2 hours in refrigerator.
Flavors combine best if left to marinate overnight.
Before serving, drain.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Stir and heat the first 3 ingredients over medium heat until it forms soft ball in cold water.
Then remove from heat and add peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Combine eggs, yolks, half and half and seasonings; stir in cheese.
Sprinkle bacon in shell.
Gently pour custard over.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes, until custard puffs.

title: mexican cornbread(serves 8)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except cheese. Put half of the mixture in a greased 9-inch square pan.
Then put 1/2 cup cheese on top.
Pour in the remaining batter.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: blushing pink frozen salad
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add lemon juice and sugar, then all other ingredients, folding in whipped cream last.
Freeze overnight.

title: pimiento biscuits
directions: Mix all together with spoon.
Dip mixture out onto cookie sheet in small mounds.
Bake at 450° about 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 12 biscuits.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Mix sugar, salt, milk and oleo. Bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes. Remove from heat; add marshmallows and mix until they are melted. Add vanilla, graham cracker crumbs and pecans. Mix and drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: peanut butter icing
directions: Mix with beater.
Keep icing refrigerated.
Cake must be cool. After icing the cake, keep refrigerated.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk over low heat.
Mix nuts, coconut, raisins, chopped cherries and crushed graham crackers.
Stir in marshmallow mixture.
Mix well.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Prepare pudding following package directions.
Mix with Cool Whip.
Cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish with whole graham crackers.
Spread half of pudding mixture over crackers; then add another layer of crackers.
Spread remaining pudding mixture and top with a layer of crackers.
Refrigerate overnight.
Spread with chocolate frosting and refrigerate.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix melted fat, molasses and sugar until smooth, then add the sour milk and mix.
Add lemon extract.
Add the sifted dry ingredients and mix to a stiff dough.
Chill.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut as desired.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix eggs and sugar thoroughly.
Add cream and evaporated milk. Mix well.
Add milk and vanilla.
Stir.
Pour into freezer and churn or plug in.
Makes 1 gallon of ice cream.

title: favorite muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease bottom of 12 medium muffin cups or use paper liners.
Beat egg.
Stir in milk and oil.
Mix in remaining ingredients just until flour is moistened.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown. Remove from pan immediately.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: granola
directions: Mix together oats, coconut, wheat germ and cashews.
Set aside.
Mix oil, honey, water and vanilla.
Pour over dry ingredients, coating thoroughly.

title: apple crunch
directions: Place apples in greased pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sift together flour, sugar, salt and baking powder. Add egg and mix well.
Add walnuts, if desired.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over apples.
Combine butter and lemon juice and pour over crumbs.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: ginger glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots in boiling water until tender.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Drain carrots.
Add sauce and toss to coat.
Serves 4.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown sausage and drain grease.
Line pan with French bread. Spread sausage evenly over bread.
Spread cheese over sausage. Scramble together eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over bread in pan.
Soak overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: cottage pie
directions: Brown meat and onion in medium skillet.
Cook until beef is no longer pink and onion is tender.
Prepare mashed potatoes according to package directions, season with salt and pepper. Spoon meat mixture into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Cover with a thick layer of potatoes and top with cheese.
Bake at 350°
for 20 to 25 minutes, or until heated thoroughly and cheese is melted.

title: skinny shake and bake
directions: Combine all dry ingredients; slowly add oil.
Toss to mix. Place in airtight container.
Store in refrigerator.
Keeps for months.

title: barbecued wieners
directions: Brown onions in butter.
Add all other ingredients but frankfurters and simmer for about 5 minutes.
Punch holes in frankfurters and add to sauce.
Simmer until wieners are cooked.

title: cheese soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
